<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Natural Gas for Vehicles in Canada:  A Study of Market Penetration  Problems.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #1781"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Natural Gas for Vehicles in Canada:  A Study of Market Penetration  Problems.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Natural Gas for Vehicles in Canada:  A Study of Market Penetration  Problems.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Sumner, Brian D.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Calgary, Alta., Canadian Energy Research Institute, 57 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Natural gas vehicle (NGV) markets in Italy, New Zealand, the United States and Canada are compared.  The purpose of the study is to identify reasons why natural gas is an attractive fuel for vehicles in Italy and New Zealand, while Canada and the U.S. app
ear to resist a changeover.  The research indicates a number of quite serious obstacles preventing natural gas becoming the fuel of choice for potential vehicle converters and recommendations which aim to overcome these obstacles are suggested
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

CANADA,ITALY,MARKET,NEW ZEALAND
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
539<P>

<P><HR>We apologize that for copyright reasons, BCRI is unable to provide copies of any article catalogued here.  For further information contact <A HREF="mailto:inglis@bcr.bc.ca">Alan Inglis</A>, CATF Database Coordinator.<BR>

