<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Research of Acoustic Emissions in Natural Gas Vehicle Storage Cylinders.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2143"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Research of Acoustic Emissions in Natural Gas Vehicle Storage Cylinders.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Research of Acoustic Emissions in Natural Gas Vehicle Storage Cylinders.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Carter, S.A.; CNG Fuel Systems<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Ottawa, Ont. : Transport Canada, TP9470E.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
October 30, 1987<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

This is a detailed report on a project aimed at validating Acoustic Emission Testing as a means of detecting active cracking in compressed natural gas vehicle storage cylinders.  The report includes the procedure followed, the results obtained, and the fi
nal conclusions drawn from th testing.  Results indicated that acoustic emission testing was able t detect stress corrosion cracking, with activity levels very sensitive to cylinder pressure.  However, AET may not be able to predict an impending burst.  (
author abstract
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

CORROSION,STORAGE,TANK
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
1993<P>

<P><HR>We apologize that for copyright reasons, BCRI is unable to provide copies of any article catalogued here.  For further information contact <A HREF="mailto:inglis@bcr.bc.ca">Alan Inglis</A>, CATF Database Coordinator.<BR>

