<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>The Development of Dual Fuel Engines for Powers above l,500 bhp.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2411"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>The Development of Dual Fuel Engines for Powers above l,500 bhp.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
The Development of Dual Fuel Engines for Powers above l,500 bhp.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Hopkins, V.H.F.; Talbutt, R.J.; Whitehouse, N.D.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
No source given, 15 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

This article discusses early design and development of the four-stroke cycle dual fuel engine which burns gaseous fuel and/or fuel oil.  The development of two ranges of dual fuel engines from their early naturally aspirated form to their supercharged des
ign are described.  The power range covered is from 165 bhp to 2,104 bhp
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

DESIGN,DUAL-FUEL,ENGINE,SUPERCHARGER
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
584<P>

