<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Safe Use of Efficient, High Pressure Gas Cylinders.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2179"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Safe Use of Efficient, High Pressure Gas Cylinders.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Safe Use of Efficient, High Pressure Gas Cylinders.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Irani, R.S.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Metals and Materials, 3(6):333-338, 1987.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

High pressure gas cylinders are used in diverse applications, ranging from steelmaking and chemical processing to sub-aqua diving.  It is important for industrial gas companies to maintain high standards of cylinder safety while also ensuring high efficie
ncy, cost-effectiveness and convenience.  In this article specifications, standards and regulations relating to the design, manufacture and transportation of cylinders are discussed.  The author emphasises the importance of cylinder maintenance and inspec
tion in ensuring long service life, and considers features which should be taken into account in enhancing the effectiveness of the cylinder package as a means of gas transportation.  (Author Abstract)
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

DEVICE,INSPECTION,MAINTENANCE,REGULATIONS,SAFETY,STORAGE,TANK
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
1286<P>

<P><HR>We apologize that for copyright reasons, BCRI is unable to provide copies of any article catalogued here.  For further information contact <A HREF="mailto:inglis@bcr.bc.ca">Alan Inglis</A>, CATF Database Coordinator.<BR>

