<H1>Ranger Goes Natural</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Ranger Goes Natural<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Kitzner, Ernie<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Engineering World, Ford Motor Company, Vol. 9, No. 3, 2 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Operation of America's first factory-built vehicles modified to run on natural gas began in April when Ford Motor company delivered a test fleet of 27 specially equipped 1984 Ranger pickup trucks to major gas utilities and other natural gas-related compan
ies
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

CONVERSION,FORD,TRUCK
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
262<P>

