<TITLE>Natural Gas for Vehicles Development Plan, 1987-1992.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #1776"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Natural Gas for Vehicles Development Plan, 1987-1992.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Natural Gas for Vehicles Development Plan, 1987-1992.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Canadian Gas Association.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Don Mills, ON, Canadian Gas Association, Oct. 1987.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

The NGV Development Plan sets out the strategies and programs which the Canadian NGV industry plans to adopt in order to reach its projected goals. Although the rate of conversions dropped in 1987, when gasoline prices declined, the total number was only
slightly less than in 1985.  It is necessary that industry and government continue their support of natural gas as a vehicle fuel and that strong marketing programs continue.  Research and development is an integral part of the NGV Development Plan
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

CANADA,COMPRESSED,CONVERSION,ENERGY,NATURAL GAS,POLICY,REFUELLING,STATION,TANK
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
1315<P>

