<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Safety Aspects Of Natural Gas Locomotives.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2182"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Safety Aspects Of Natural Gas Locomotives.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Safety Aspects Of Natural Gas Locomotives.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Young, Y.D.; Driscoll, M.L.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Energy Work Shop: Alternative Fuels Safety, 1985 RTAC Annual Conference,  Vancouver, B.C., Sept. 30-Oct. 3, 7 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
September 30, 1985<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

This paper discusses safety aspects involved in the testing program of Burlington Northern Railroad's dual fuel (diesel/natural gas) locomotive, as well as concerns for future CNG or dual fuel locomotive research.  Burlington Northern's in-service testing
program requires exemption from tw U.S. Dept. of Transport regulations concerning transportation of hazardous substances before it can continue.  Railroad personnel have already been given guidelines for making safety checks of potential hazards however.
Concerns to be considered in the future include safe design plans for tender cars, and the possibility of natural gas being released and accumulating in railway tunnels
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

DEVICE,DUAL-FUEL,LOCOMOTIVE,SAFETY
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
780<P>

