<B>Authors: </B>
Natural Gas Vehicle Task Force<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
British Columbia. Science Council. Energy Sector Planning Committee.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Environmental, economic and national energy security issues have resulted in a rapidly growing interest worldwide in natural gas for vehicles (NGV). British Columbia can capitalize on this interest by supporting a focused technological development strateg
y specifically targeted at marketable products and processes which can be developed and manufactured in B.C.  This report describes general areas of required support, but focuses on these specific products for Science Council support: the non-metallic, on
-board NGV storage cylinder; the direct injection natural gas fuel storage cylinder injection system for heavy-duty engines; the dual fuel diesel/natural gas retrofit system; and the small, on-site residential or small commercial NGV refueling compressor.
