<H1>Natural Gas the New Locomotive Fuel.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Natural Gas the New Locomotive Fuel.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Tuskey, Lee W.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Nonpetroleum Vehicular Fuel Symposium IV, Arlington, Va., April 16-18.   (DE84 901824), 29 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
April 16, 1984<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Tests on a locomotive diesel engine converted to dual fuel (CNG/diesel) are run to determine if the dual fuel engine in a railway service, will provide high performance and lower fuel and maintenance costs.  After completion of static tests the locomotive
will be tested in line haul railway service.  If successful, large amounts of actual data for analysis of comparable locomotive performance, will be available
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

CONVERSION,DUAL-FUEL,LOCOMOTIVE
