<H1>PG&E Researches Their NGV Market.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
PG&E Researches Their NGV Market.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Anon.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Advanced Vehicle News, 15(1):21 (Feb).<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

The Pacific Gas and Electric Company of California is moving into its second stage of involvement with the NGV industry -- a program for conversion of customer fleets.  They have examined market influences such as safety, economics, and equipment required
, and taken into consideration concerns of the customers in the development of their marketing strategy.  PG&E also undertook an extensive in-house marketing program to educate their own employees on the advantages of natural gas vehicles.  They believe t
hat developing a successful in-house NGV program is crucial to marketing CNG to fleet owners in their area
<P>

