<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Propane Tank Anti-Boiling Liquid Evaporating Vapour Explosion (BLEVE)  Safety System</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2050"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Propane Tank Anti-Boiling Liquid Evaporating Vapour Explosion (BLEVE)  Safety System</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Propane Tank Anti-Boiling Liquid Evaporating Vapour Explosion (BLEVE)  Safety System<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Young, Colin G.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Gaseous Fuels for Transportation I, Vancouver, B.C., August 7-10, 1986 pp 1193-1198  (B.C. Research -- Institute of Gas Technology)<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

A propane tank anti-BLEVE (boiling liquid evaporating vapour explosion) safety system is presented.  BLEVE occurs when a propane tank is engulfed in a fire.  The top of the tank becomes hot and weakened causing the tank to rupture due to the explosive nat
ure of the high pressure fuel in the tank.  The system is designed for rail and road propane tankers and storage tanks, but can also be used on automotive propane tanks.  The system has a simple turbo-charger inside the tank and uses the vapour escaping t
hrough the pressure safety relief valve to spin the turbo-charger that takes in liquid propane just below the surface near the shell of the tank, and sprays it vertically upwards to cool the top part of the tank.  For mobile tanks, the design uses gravity
valve assemblies to ensure that the liquid is sprayed upwards inside the tank and vapour is released upwards outside the tank.  The system is also suitable for use with other fuels, and for low pressure tanks.  (From author abstract
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

DEVICE,FIRE,SAFETY
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
1162<P>

<P><HR>We apologize that for copyright reasons, BCRI is unable to provide copies of any article catalogued here.  For further information contact <A HREF="mailto:inglis@bcr.bc.ca">Alan Inglis</A>, CATF Database Coordinator.<BR>

