<TITLE>The role of natural gas as a cleaner vehicle fuel</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2589"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>The role of natural gas as a cleaner vehicle fuel</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
The role of natural gas as a cleaner vehicle fuel<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Bill Hennessey<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
BC Gas<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
March 6, 1995<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

This paper discusses in detail the role of natural gas as a cleaner vehicle fuel. It gives the advantages of using natural gas as a fuel. The NGV is the lowest emitting production vehicle and that the NGV conversion technology has improved dramatically to
allow converted vehicles to meet present gasoline vehicle emission standards. Natural gas has essentially the same potential for renewable supply as ethanol or methanol and emits fewer fine particulates, the single major cause of health effects from vehi
cle emissions. (summary)
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

EMISSIONS,HEAVY VEHICLE,LIGHT VEHICLE,NATURAL GAS,NGV,ULEV
