<TITLE>The First European Parking Facility Open to the Public for the Exchange of Thermal and Electrical Cars</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2453"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>The First European Parking Facility Open to the Public for the Exchange of Thermal and Electrical Cars</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
The First European Parking Facility Open to the Public for the Exchange of Thermal and Electrical Cars<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
F. Massimello, G. Brusaglino<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Symposium Proceedings, Vol. 1, Sessions 1A-2D, The 12th International Electric Vehicle Symposium (EVS-12) and Electric Vehicle Exposition.  pp 191-200<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
December 5, 1994<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Since november 10, 1993, an interchange car park is in operation in the city of Livomo with five electric vehicles to be used by the customers on a SELF-SERVICE basis, through a prepaid MICROCHIP CARD.  The parking lots are equipped with electronic column
s for battery charging and for "dialogue" with the customer.  The initiative has the aims of spreading knowledge of electirc vehicles making them available to any private individual without entailing the problems of ownership, to analyse the type of missi
ons accomplished via free use of EVs, to verify the acceptance/appreciation of EVs and of this type of service and to encourage use of EVs in the urban context.The results are positive, with good response of the systems in terms of reliability and sui
tability for the needs of a fair number of users.  Plans are in progress for installing interchange car parks of the same type in other italian cities.
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

ANALYSIS,CONSUMER,ELECTRIC,ITALY,RELIABILITY,THERMAL
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
5244<P>

