<H1>Natural Gas:  The Ideal Fuel For Diesel Engines.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Natural Gas:  The Ideal Fuel For Diesel Engines.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Bollina, E.; Basaglia, R.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
GasTech 85, LNG/LPG Conference, Nice, France, Nov. 12-15, pp. 352-356.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
November 12, 1995<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

The importance of natural gas as a substitute for diesel fuel is discussed.  A brief summary of key results of scientific research and statistical studies conducted worldwide have been compiled and are included.  Reduced emissions and fuel costs are expec
ted to be the primary advantages resulting from the development of the technology
