<H1>Present British Developments in Alternative Fuel Vehicle Fuels.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Present British Developments in Alternative Fuel Vehicle Fuels.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Thompson, J.K.L.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Nonpetroleum Vehicular Fuels III, Oct. 12-14, 17 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

This paper covers in brief format the energy situation in Britain, the government's energy policy and current work on alternative fuels.  The main alternative fuels considered in Britain are alcohols, either for use as blending components or as 'neat' fue
l, liquefied natural gas, liquid petroleum gas, hydrogen, oil from coal and other petrol 'extenders'.  This paper does not attempt to cover all the work being done in Britain, or provide comprehensive technical and commercial information, it is merely an
overview of the industry
<P>

