<H1>NGV - an international perspective.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
NGV - an international perspective.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Potts, Ronald E.E.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Presented at the First International Conference and Exhibition, Sydney,  Australia, Oct. 27-30, 1988.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
October 27, 1988<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

The marketing environment for NGV is characterized by unpredictable and dynamic international forces which have impeded its development.  This environmental instability has created great uncertainty and when coupled with a depressed international oil mark
et and a general trend toward fisca restraint by many of the more developed nations, has resulted in the prevalence of a "wait and see" attitude among government and industry officials alike.  Yet, there are some success stories and there is an internatio
nal awareness of NGV.  It is reported that more than 40 countries have active NGV programs (From author's paper Includes brief author biography.  9 refs
<P>

