<TITLE>Natural Gas Vehicle Marketing Activities in the United States - 1986.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #1753"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Natural Gas Vehicle Marketing Activities in the United States - 1986.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Natural Gas Vehicle Marketing Activities in the United States - 1986.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Seisler, J.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Gaseous Fuels for Transportation I, Vancouver, B.C., August 7-10, 1986, pp 101-113  (B.C. Research -- Institute of Gas Technology)<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

This 1986 status report on the marketing of natural gas vehicles (NGVs) in the United States summarizes activities of the natural gas utility industry and of the manufacturers of NGV equipment and installers.  The number of gas utilites marketing NGVs is
growing.  However while some utilities are developing marketing strategies and aggressively promoting NGVs, other companies are yet-to-be-convinced of the economic and technical viability of NGVs.  U.S. NGV equipment manufacturers and installers continue
to struggle in a marketplace dominated by reduced oil prices and approximately 10% growth in the number of conversions nationally.  Barriers such as expensive liability insurance, government regulations, and a general lack of a federal government alternat
ive fuels policy continue to thwart the NGV industry.  However, industry and government funding of research, coupled with tough environmental vehicle emission standards are benefitting the NGV commercialization efforts.  Manufacturers of original equipmen
t generally remain unconvinced of the market viability of NGVs however some NGV research and marketing is being conducted.  (From author abstract
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

MARKETING,UNITED STATES
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
1098<P>

<P><HR>We apologize that for copyright reasons, BCRI is unable to provide copies of any article catalogued here.  For further information contact <A HREF="mailto:inglis@bcr.bc.ca">Alan Inglis</A>, CATF Database Coordinator.<BR>

