<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Natural Gas Vehicles Get a Boost.</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #1757"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>Natural Gas Vehicles Get a Boost.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Natural Gas Vehicles Get a Boost.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Watts, J.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Pipeline & Gas Journal, v. 215(4):48-49, Apr. 1989.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

The slow but steady growth of natural gas as a vehicle fuel in the U.S. has received a boost with the formation of the Natural Gas Vehicle Coalition.  The group of 30 natural gas companies and automotive equipment suppliers was established to promote the
use of natural gas vehicles as an environmentally and economically preferable option to gasoline and diesel models.  (from author abstract
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

MARKETING
