<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>The Prospects for NGV in the Asian Region</TITLE> 
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="AutoGen by Bayleaf Software Inc."> 
<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Citation #2520"> 
</HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>
<H1>The Prospects for NGV in the Asian Region</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
The Prospects for NGV in the Asian Region<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
E.M. Yeaman , I.D. Moncriff, A.R. Campbell<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Liquid Fuels Management Group Limited, Welligton, New Zealand<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
November 30, 1899<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Predominatly, the market prospects for NGV will be determined by fuel price relativities, the competitive margin between the delivered cost of Compressed Natural Gas (CNG) / Liquid Natural Gas (LNG) and the established gasoline or diesel options. This pap
er presents a discussion of the issues and influences which determine these relativities, reflecting the macro-economic analysis which is involved in setting national energy policy. The context for this discussion is the Asian region, for which the energy
situation is particularly dynamic, with gas being of increasing prominence.Following is a review of the gas supply and value characteristics and influence prevailing in the region, and its consequent opportunity as a fuel for vehicle use.
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
5583<P>

