<H1>Optimization of Propane Engines for Light Duty Vehicles - Phase I.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
Optimization of Propane Engines for Light Duty Vehicles - Phase I.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
Chrysler Canada Ltd.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Ottawa, Transport Canada, Transportation Development Centre, TP 5171E, 162 pp.<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Propane information collected from hardware manufacturers, fleet managers, technical papers and reports was compiled and analyzed.  Results indicate that propane technology is significantly inferior to that of gasoline and that specific areas need improve
ment.  The foremost problem is engine valve recession, others include fuel efficiency, refueling techniques and hardware and cold weather operating characteristics.  This study recommends a R & D program to address these subjects and includes an outline o
f suggested testing procedures and recommended priorities
<P>

<B>Keywords: </B>

PROPANE,RESEARCH
<BR><B>File Reference: </B>
