<H1>New Solubility Data on Methane in Structured Liquids - Water and Organic  Liquids.</H1><HR>

<B>Title: </B>
New Solubility Data on Methane in Structured Liquids - Water and Organic  Liquids.<BR>

<B>Authors: </B>
O'Brien, R.N.<BR>

<B>Source: </B>
Gaseous Fuels for Transportation I, Vancouver, B.C., August 7-10, 1986, pp 459-475  (B.C. Research -- Institute of Gas Technology)<BR>

<B>Date: </B>
<P>

<B>Abstract: </B><BR>

Henry's Law constants for methane in water have been checked for pressures in the region where hydrate-clathrate formation should begin.  Laser interferometry has been used to check for density gradients and natural convection.  Methane solubilities in se
veral structured organic liquids have also been measured and the effects of structure assessed both in increased solubility and decreased rate of evolution on pressure release.  Results suggest higher solubilities and slower pressure release.  (From autho
r abstract
