<TITLE>Jumanji</TITLE>

<META NAME="SUBJECT" CONTENT="Motion Picture Studio Facilities at BCRI">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Michael Barrick">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../gifs/film_bg.gif" BGCOLOR="#CCCCCC" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#000040" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="../gifs/strip.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=128 HEIGHT=922></IMG>
<IMG SRC="../gifs/hdr_film.gif" border=0 WIDTH=464 HEIGHT=93></IMG><P>

<H1>Jumanji</H1>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bann02.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<IMG SRC="jumanji.gif" WIDTH=450 HEIGHT=351><p>
Picture of the house that was built and flooded for scenes in the movie "Jumanji."
<A NAME="water"></A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="robinal.gif" WIDTH=450 HEIGHT=307><P>
The scene called for Williams's character to leap into the water and jump onto the crocodile's back to divert it from attacking the others. The actor did several takes, each funnier than the last...
<P>
The whole cast spent entire shooting days in the water, which was heated to 90 degrees when it was circulated to keep the actors and technicians as warm as possible. "I got used to coming to work every day and putting on my wetsuit," says Bonnie Hunt. "It was quite glamorous and I got my aerobic workout during our many water ballets. Half the crew was in with us, so it was a family affair."
<P>
(From <A HREF="http://www.spe.sony.com/Pictures/SonyMovies/Jumanji/production.html">
http://www.spe.sony.com/Pictures/SonyMovies/Jumanji/production.html</A>)
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/ban_fade.gif" HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0><BR>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/redball.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> For further information you
may email Jay Code at <A HREF="mailto:code@bcr.bc.ca">code@bcr.bc.ca</A>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/ban_fade.gif" HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0><BR>
