<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>CATF Review Newletter: Issue No. 22 (July, 1995)</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Andrea Gomory">
<!-- Last Update: 01/10/96 -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#E629A">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<BODY>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catf_pg2.gif"><BR>

<!-- begin table--><!-- total=630 -->
<table border=0 width=630 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr>
<td width=150 valign=top rowspan=1>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=6 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="niche.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_1.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="ballard.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_2.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="online.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_3.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="gotran.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_4b.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="students.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_5.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="afv.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_6.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="ngv.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="22toc_7.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
</td>

<td valign=top colspan=2 width=480>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The bus has a 240 horsepower Cummins L10G engine running on natural gas only, with spark ignition. The engine has analogue electronics.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The vehicle is equipped with two 100 U.S. gallon Cryenco cryogenic tanks with 20% ullage and a pumpless fuel conditioning system. The bus is fuelled once a day; it has a total effective capacity of about 150 U.S. gallons of LNG, which gives the bus a range of about 500km (say 300 miles) The storage tanks are located underneath the bus; the frame rails had to be widened slightly to accommodatethe two 18&quot; tanks. The installation was carried out to the
Canadian Standards Association's Z-276 standard, and it has five gas detectors and a fire suppression system.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The fuelling station was designed by Liquid Carbonic. Gas is not liquefied on site, but is trucked in, currently from Laporte, Indiana. The station is pumpless, with all gas pressure resulting
from the vapour pressure of the LNG. It has 6000 gallons of main cryogenic storage, and is capable of a 30-50 gallons/minute dispensing rate. With a 500 gallon conditioning unit, it could refuel up
to 40 buses per day, and it is expandable beyond that.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Usually, the bus can be fuelled with 150 gallons of LNG in four to five minutes. Excess vapourized fuel from storage boil-off is compressed and stored in a tube trailer at 2250 psi for CNG use.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
When the bus is parked, boil-off results in a pressure rise of about 1 psi/hr at 20 degrees Celsius when the tanks are 3/4 full. The bus is fully instrumented, with pressures and temperatures being recorded constantly.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The bus was first filled on April 6th, 1995, and entered revenue service towards the end of May. No problems have been reported in the operation of either the bus or the fuelling station so
far.<BR>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><A HREF="gotran.htm"><IMG align=left BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/back.gif"></A></td>
<td><br></td>
<td width=480><br></td>
</tr>
</table>
