<!DOCTYPE HTML"-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN">
<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>CATF Review Newletter: Issue No. 21 (April, 1995)</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Andrea Gomory">
<!-- Last Update: 01/10/96 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#E629A">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<BODY>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catf_pg4.gif"><BR>

<!-- begin table--><!-- total=630 -->
<table border=0 width=630 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>

<tr>
<td width=150 valign=top rowspan=1>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=6 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="hybrid.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_1b.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="dimethyl.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_2.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="cng_fuel.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_3.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="notes.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_4.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="alt_fuel.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_5.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
</td>


<td valign=top colspan=2 width=480>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Power</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
HEV power is characterized by the electric motors advantage of very high accelerative torque at very low speeds. In parallel hybrids, this is blended with the internal combustion engine characteristic of high torque at higher speeds. The ICE can be used to supplement the electric motor on demand, or vice versa, depending on the relative size of the two units, and battery storage capacity.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Capacity</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
Less batteries, smaller ICEs, and electric motors smaller than ICEs may all increase interior room. However, like any vehicle designed for great efficiency, low weight is vital. In the end, the performance, economy, and emissions of any vehicle depends on the payload it is carrying.<BR>


<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Cost</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
HEVs, because they are more complex than either conventionally powered vehicles or electric vehicles, would probably be more expensive than either. However, since a large proportion of the purchase cost, and the operating cost, of an electric vehicle lies in the purchase and periodic replacement of large numbers of batteries, an HEV that needed less batteries might be cheaper. And if an HEV could be made using mostly production parts and assembly techniques (which might be possible if it didnt have to carry too many batteries) it could be cheaper than an EV built in small quantities.<BR>


<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Potential</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
What is the HEVs potential? The HEV is poised to utilize advances in both ICE technology and electric vehicle and battery technology. Its clear that HEV design strategy involves an extremely complex set of trade-offs, together with a very clear idea of what functions the vehicle will be expected to perform. Technological breakthroughs may well initiate rethinking of those tradeoffs, as well as increasing the application of hybrid vehicles. Hybrid buses have already been built. So the hybrid approach will probably not be limited to urban commuter vehicles; the potential is much greater than that of the electric vehicles from which current thinking is derived.<BR>



</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><A HREF="Hybrid_3.htm"><IMG align=left BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/back.gif"></A></td>
<td><br></td>
<td width=480>
<br></td>
</tr>
</table>
<!-- end of table-->

