<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>CATF Review Newletter: Issue No. 23 (October, 1995)</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Andrea Gomory">
<!-- Last Update: 01/10/96 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#E629A">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<BODY>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catf_pg3.gif"><BR>

<!-- begin table--><!-- total=630 -->
<table border=0 width=630 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>

<tr>
<td width=150 valign=top rowspan=1>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=6 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="hd_lean.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_1b.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="LEVs.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_2.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="Chilling.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_3.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="NGV_pres.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_4.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="CGA_send.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_5.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
</td>


<td valign=top colspan=2 width=480>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Electronic engine control unit</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
The electronic control system will be based on the ECOJET system developed by Mogas Sales Inc. for light duty vehicles. This system utilizes a 68332 chip in the control module. This will be connected via a 19.2 kilobyte RS232 port to a personal computer, thus enabling the control chip to be reprogrammed and also operating data and sensor readings to be monitored in real time.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The 68332 has 256K of RAM, and onboard EPROM and flash EPROM to facilitate reprogramming from the PC while under way.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The ECOJET system is also capable of adaptive learning, and this capability will be employed in optimizing the engines operation.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Flywheel and camshaft gear sensors will provide the base timing for electronic control of all engine events, and a solid state ignition system will utilize spark plugs located in the former injector ports of an experimental cylinder head, originally made by Cummins for natural gas use.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Oxygen sensors</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
The exhaust manifold has two groups of three pipes, and a single wide-spectrum Horiba type oxygen sensor will be used in each group. The advantage of the wide spectrum sensor 
is that it will give a series of digital signals marking variations in the exhaust oxygen content, rather than the on/off signal which emanates from a conventional sensor. This enables the ECU to detect trends in oxygen content much more quickly, and results in more efficient and quicker adaptation to changing engine conditions.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Instrumentation</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
As a research project, this engine will be thoroughly instrumented, with particular attention to the propane fuel system and 
individual cylinder pressure sensing. Initial testing and development will be carried out on BCRI's large engine dynamometer, which has extensive facilities for real-time data collection.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Engine completed by spring</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
The first phase of the project, engine development, is expected to be completed 
by spring 1996. After that, the engine will 
be installed in an operating heavy-duty truck. The second phase, road testing, is expected 
to take about a year.<BR>


</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><A HREF="HD_lean2.htm"><IMG align=left BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/back.gif"></A></td>
<td><br></td>
<td width=480><br></td>
</tr>
</table>
