<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>CATF Review Newletter: Issue No. 23 (October, 1995)</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Andrea Gomory">
<!-- Last Update: 01/10/96 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#E629A">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<BODY>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catf_pg3.gif"><BR>

<!-- begin table--><!-- total=630 -->
<table border=0 width=630 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>

<tr>
<td width=150 valign=top rowspan=1>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=6 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="hd_lean.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_1.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="LEVs.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_2b.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="Chilling.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_3.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="NGV_pres.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_4.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="CGA_send.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_5.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
</td>

<td valign=top colspan=2 width=480>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The authors then go on to cite a number of climatic adaptations that have been demonstrated and which overcome any tendency that LEVs and ZEVs (battery powered ones in particular) might have to lose their utility in severe winter weather. Many of these will be recognised as higher tech variations on those old Canadian standbys, the block heater and the battery heater.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=8 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Technologies galore</b></font><BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
Although the study expresses considerable optimism about the future of battery-powered electric vehicles, it covers a bewildering range of technologies that have potential for the LEV or ZEV of the future, even the relatively near future. There are, of course, many battery technologies; the authors observe that potential battery powered vehicle range is on a converging course with average daily vehicle mileage. While they do not anticipate that a battery-powered journey from Calgary to Winnipeg in mid-January will soon be possible, they point out that the majority of trips, in Canada as elsewhere, are short and urban. While they admit that range is a factor, they do not see it as a problem.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Beyond batteries, the authors catalogue an astonishing variety of alternative fuels, all providing various combinations of economy, reductions in harmful emissions, reductions in greenhouse gas emissions, power and range. There are also fuel cells, hybrids, and diesels, all with their special advantages and potentials.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Fitzpatrick, Hayden and Walsh feel they have good reason to be optimistic about the progress being made in all these technologies.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=8 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Efficiencythe common thread</b></font><BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
The study reflects two common threads that underly the authors conclusions: that both motive power units and the vehicles themselves will become more efficient, and that virtually all of the technologies cited are young and full of potential. All in all, a very hopeful theme.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Copies of the study can be obtained from the CCME Task Force Secretariat at (819) 994-1641.<BR>



</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><A HREF="LEVs_pg2.htm"><IMG align=left BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/back.gif"></A></td>
<td><br></td>
<td width=480><br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<!-- end of table-->

<IMG align=top align=right vspace=1 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><br>
<IMG align=top align=left width=630 height=5 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_catf.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top align=right vspace=1 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><br>

<A HREF="../default.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/cr_home.gif" ALT="Review Homepage"></A>
<A HREF="/catf/default.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catfhome.gif" ALT="CATF Homepage"></A>
<A HREF="/default.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/bcrihome.gif" ALT="BCRI Homepage"></A>
<A HREF="/enviro/cln_tr_s.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/clean_t.gif" ALT="BCRI Clean Transportation"></A>
