<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>CATF Review Newletter: Issue No. 23 (October, 1995)</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Andrea Gomory">
<!-- Last Update: 01/10/96 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#E629A">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<BODY>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catf_pg2.gif"><BR>

<!-- begin table--><!-- total=630 -->
<table border=0 width=630 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>

<tr>
<td width=150 valign=top rowspan=1>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=6 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="hd_lean.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_1b.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="LEVs.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_2.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="Chilling.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_3.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="NGV_pres.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_4.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="CGA_send.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="23toc_5.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
</td>

<td valign=top colspan=2 width=480>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
So this project involves new technology in several areas:<BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=12 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"> <IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">high turbulence combustion chamber design<br>
<IMG align=top hspace=12 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"> <IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">electronic engine management, with adaptive learning<br>
<IMG align=top hspace=12 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"> <IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">use of wide-spectrum oxygen sensors<br>
<IMG align=top hspace=12 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"> <IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">electronic turbo wastegate<BR>

<IMG align=top vspace=8 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Cummins 8.3 litre engine will have high turbulence combustion chambers</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
Cummins supplied a C8.3 six cylinder engine, along with a spare cylinder head, and piston blanks. This is normally a diesel engine, but Cummins does market a version for operation on natural gas. The combustion chamber of the engine is a bowl-in-piston design, with zero deck clearance and a flat machined face on the cylinder head.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
The engine has a log manifold and a turbocharger in its diesel form.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Mechanical Engineering professor Dr. Robert Evans of the University of British Columbia designed a new, very high turbulence combustion chamber (UBC Squish Jet Combustion Chamber) which has been machined into the pistons. The combustion chamber has a number of features to promote a high degree of mixing of fuel and air, essential to successful lean-burn operation. The compression ratio, 9.25:1, must be viewed in the light of a maximum turbocharger pressure of 16 to 18 psi.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<font size=3><b>Direct propane injection</b></font><BR>
<IMG align=top vspace=2 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
Precise fuel control is sought through the use of fuel injectors. These will be located just upstream of each intake port. While the log manifold is probably not ideal for equal air distribution between the cylinders, the control system will be designed so that the injector pulse width on each cylinder can be tuned, while the engine is running, using electronic controls and an external PC, to optimize the performance of each individual cylinder. A custom-built mass flow sensor will be used to monitor airflow.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
This approach also has interesting potential from a research point of view. Effectively, the researchers have the equivalent of six separately controlled (and separately instrumented) cylinders in a single engine.<BR>

</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><A HREF="HD_lean.htm"><IMG align=left BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/back.gif"></A></td>
<td><br></td>
<td width=480>
<A HREF="HD_lean3.htm"><IMG align=right BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/forward.gif"></A>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<!-- end of table-->

<IMG align=top align=right vspace=1 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><br>
<IMG align=top align=left width=630 height=5 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_catf.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top align=right vspace=1 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><br>

<A HREF="../default.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/cr_home.gif" ALT="Review Homepage"></A>
<A HREF="/catf/default.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catfhome.gif" ALT="CATF Homepage"></A>
<A HREF="/default.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/bcrihome.gif" ALT="BCRI Homepage"></A>
