<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>CATF Review Newletter: Issue No. 21 (April, 1995)</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta>
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Andrea Gomory">
<!-- Last Update: 01/10/96 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#E629A">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<BODY>
<IMG border=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/catf_pg2.gif"><BR>

<!-- begin table--><!-- total=630 -->
<table border=0 width=630 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>

<tr>
<td width=150 valign=top rowspan=1>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=6 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="hybrid.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_1.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="dimethyl.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_2b.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="cng_fuel.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_3.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="notes.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_4.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thik.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="alt_fuel.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="21toc_5.gif"></A><br>
<IMG border=0 align=top SRC="../cr_gifs/toc_thin.gif"><BR>
</td>

<td valign=top colspan=2 width=480>
<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
DME is mainly used today as an aerosol propellant, as a replacement for CFC gases, which were found to be harmful to the earths ozone layer. Currently, total world production is around 150,000 metric tonnes per day, and it is made from methanol by a dehydration process.<BR>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Haldor Topsoe A/S have investigated the possibility of alternative methods of manufacturing DME, since the present method results in DME being inherently more expensive than methanol as a vehicle fuel. The company proposes that the two processes, the manufacture of methanol from natural gas, and the manufacture of DME from methanol, be combined. The two reactions appear to have some thermodynamic synergy, under relatively low pressures and appropriate catalysts.<br>

<IMG border=0 align=top vspace=3 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif"><BR>
<IMG align=top hspace=10 SRC="../cr_gifs/dot_clr.gif">
Haldor Topsoe say that the retail price of DME, taking into account manufacturing and distribution costs, should not be unduly above the comparable diesel price, when taking into account the environmental benefits from the use of DME. However, the company warns that very large DME plants would be required, in  areas with a low natural gas price, and also the establishment of an infrastructure for DME distribution. In a transition period, they say, there will without a doubt be a need for some government incentives for this scenario to be economically viable.<br>

</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><A HREF="dimethyl.htm"><IMG align=left BORDER=0 SRC="../cr_gifs/back.gif"></A></td>
<td><br></td>
<td width=480><br></td>
</tr>
</table>
<!-- end of table-->

