<p align=center><b><a name="netw">NETWORKS & COMMUNICATIONS</a></b></p>

<p>DEFINITION: Networks allow computers to transmit and receive data.  The technologies required to enable computer communications include: connecting devices (optical fiber, coax cable, microwaves, etc.,), switches, controllers, routers, gateway, PBX'S, communications protocols, tools for network management, network services and security features.</p>

<p align=center>HIGH-IMPACT CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTORS:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Capital Investment
    <li>Quality
    <li>Applied Research and Development
	<li>Collaboration with Academia, Government and Business
	<li>Standardization and Standards
    <li>People: Skilled Personnel
</ul>
<p align=center>MEDIUM-IMPACT CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTORS:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Critical Mass
	<li>Large Market Size
	<li>State of Art Manufacturing
	<li>Private Sector Cooperation
	<li>Basic Research
	<li>Intellectual Property Protection
     <li>Reduced Risk For Large Emerging Market
</ul>

