<p align=center><b><a name="huma">HUMAN INTERFACE</a></b></p>

<p>DEFINITION: Human-computer interface technologies make it possible for human beings to get understandable information in to or out of computers.  These can be as basic as a keyboard and mouse or as complicated as speaking to a computer and being understood or receiving a dynamically generated, animated video/audio presentation of on-line information as an answer to a question.  The technologies include: graphical user interfaces, animation and full-motion video, optical character recognition (OCR), handwriting recognition, speech (synthesis and recognition) . and natural language (particularly translation).</p>

<p align=center>HIGH-IMPACT CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTORS:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Applied Research and Development
     <li>People: Skilled Personnel
</ul>
<p align=center>MEDIUM-IMPACT CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTORS:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Collaboration with Academia, Government and Business
	<li>Basic Research
	<li>Standardization and Standards
  	<li>Intellectual Property Protection
</ul>

