Last-modified: Thursday, 07-Dec-95 18:23:28 GMT
Content-length: 884
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<html>
<title>Key Terms</title>
<p>KEY TERMS</p>
<hr>
<p>Both open and closed interfaces may involve <b>PROPRIETARY OR NONPROPRIETARY</b> technology. </p>
 
<p>"Nonproprietary" technology implies that no intellectual property rights or unilateral control are involved in connection with the use of an interface specification or the replication of the implementation to an interface specification. </p>
 
<p>"Proprietary" technology is subject to intellectual property rights or unilateral control in connection with the use of a given interface specification or the replication of its implementation. </p>
 
<p>Intellectual property rights involved in the technology of a critical open interface are available for use on reasonable terms and conditions demonstrably free of discrimination.</p>

<a href="report6.html">Return to the Main Report</a>
</html>
