<html>
<title>Goals and Benefits</title>
<h2>Goals and Benefits</h2>
<hr>
<p><b>GOAL</b>: Open interfaces between information appliances for NII applications and NII local access provider networks to help ensure that users can plug any information appliance of their choice into any local access provider's network. </p>
 
 <p><b>BENEFIT</b>: If these interfaces are open, users and providers of information services will be able to connect the information appliances of their choice to any access network, resulting in greater competition among information appliance vendors, i.e., greater choice in products, more innovation, reduced prices, and an easier to use, more convenient system.  For example, a user will be able to plug any type of information appliance -television, computer, telephone or other appliance that combines the capabilities of all three -- into the outlet provided by the chosen local access provider and use the appliance to access any of the types of services that the provider offers.</p>
<a href="report6.html">Return to the Main Report</a>
</html>
</DOC>
