<html>
<title>Goals and Benefits</title>
<h2>Goals and Benefits</h2>
<hr>
<p><b>GOAL:</b> Open interfaces between different implementations of NII information systems/services/ applications that allow the systems, services, and applications to "communicate" with each other so users can generate and receive information in various formats and media without having to make special adjustments to translate between different implementations. </p>
<p><b>BENEFIT: </b>Open interfaces between NII systems, services, and applications will enable users to take advantage of the NII's resources without having to make major adjustments when communicating with different systems.  Users will be able to send electronic messages in various formats to others, regardless of system and service differences, retrieve and interpret documents that appear exactly as composed by the author, and send queries to a variety of different databases containing information in different formats voice, text, video, multimedia without having to tailor the search request to each database or format.  For example, users on different systems will be able to conduct a multimedia videoconference to jointly revise a draft document.  They could then send the document to a publisher, who would receive it in exactly the same format as it was drafted.</p>
<a href="report6.html">Return to the Main Report</a>
</html>
