<html>
<title>Goals and Benefits</title>
<h2>Goals and Benefits</title>
<hr>
<p><b>GOAL:</b> Open interfaces between local access providers to ensure that users have maximum choice in their selection of and access to network and information services and to ensure the proper conditions for competition. </p>
<p><b>BENEFIT:</b> Open interfaces at the above points will allow different network service providers to interconnect and interoperate with each other so that users will have the greatest flexibility in choosing and accessing services and applications available through the Nil.  Similarly, information service providers will be able to reach any user, regardless of the local access provider the user or the information provider uses.  For example, a user who chooses a telephone company to provide local access service will be able to communicate -- in a variety of formats -- with a friend who obtains local service from a cable company.  They in turn will be able to communicate just as easily with friends who use competitive access providers or wireless systems.</p>
<a href="report6.html">Return to the Main Report</a>
