<head><title>Appendix F</title>
<h2>U.S. Federal Government R&D Funding Trend <br>(Defense Versus Non-Defense)</h2>
<hr>
<p>While U.S. government spending on R&D has increased significantly in absolute levels over the last 25 years, defense R&D (largely development) has shifted from a historical share of 50% of total R&D spending to a high of about 70% in 1986.  It has dropped to about 60% of federal R&D spending since then.</p>
<img src="6.gif">
<p>Source: National Science Foundation</p>
