Last-modified: Thursday, 07-Dec-95 18:18:28 GMT
Content-length: 685
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head><title>Figure 10</title>
<h2>Computer Related R&D By Government (1989)</h2>
<hr>
<p>In 1989, while the U.S. government allocated 2% of its total R&D budget to computer-related efforts, the Japanese government spent almost 5% of its R&D budget on computer-related technologies.  Germany, France and the U.K. spent an average of 6%, not including their contributions to Pan European R&D efforts.</p>
<hr>
<img src="10.gif">
<hr>
<p>Source:  Science and Engineering Indicators - 1989(NSF)<br>
AAAS Report XV, Nistep<br>
Business Week, Bain Estimate<br>
OECD Science and Technology Indicators 1989(2)<br>
Ministry of R&D (West Germany)</p>
</html>
</DOC>
