<html>
<head>
<title>Tomorrow's Leaders</title>
<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<img src="icons/title.gif">
<center>

<P>

<center>
<body bgcolor="#0000FF">
<P>

<h3><font color="#FFFF00"><em>Strathcona recognises and encourages the qualities required of tomorrow's leaders - 
competence, confidence and compassion.</em></font></h3>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Welcome to Strathcona - A Complete Education</font></h3></center>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Strathcona is dedicated to education for girls. We view education not as a narrow, exclusively intellectual experience but as a 
continual seeking of wisdom. Cultivation of the mind is crucial to this process but is incomplete without a simultaneous 
cultivation of spirit, expressed in qualities of compassion, co-operation, generosity and service.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">We aim to enable each student to discover her abilities, to develop them and to use them creatively for others. Students know 
themselves to be highly valued and learn to appreciate others through the close, personal interaction between staff members 
and girls. Our highly qualified and dedicated staff are committed to ensuring that each girl reaches her potential, both academic 
and personal. It is the spiritual dimension, with emphasis on the value of the person and the joy of learning, that gives 
Strathcona its special and important character.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Participation is a feature of the school. From the earliest years to VCE, students are encouraged to work and play together, 
make responsible choices and reflect on their actions. An environment of trust develops understanding, enthusiasm, tolerance 
and respect for one another.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Since its establishment in 1924, Strathcona's sense of community and quality of care have been constantly demonstrated 
through an outstanding pastoral care program. The school's size and diverse range of activities present opportunities for 
leadership not available in large schools. To this end every student receives leadership training and intellectual curiosity is 
nourished through innovative learning experiences.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">We want our girls to develop a passion for learning and acquire its disciplines, too. Our broad curriculum challenges students 
to think critically and creatively, identify and solve problems and communicate effectively. Scholarship in academic work is 
prized from the earliest years.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Our young women are tomorrow's leaders. They are articulate and poised, with an extraordinary positive self-image which 
derives from the knowledge that they are equipped to take their place in the rapidly changing world.</font></p><center>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><em>RUTH E BUNYAN</em></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><em>PRINCIPAL</em></font><p><img src ="icons/ruth.gif"></center>
<P><HR><P>
<I><B><font color="#FFFF00">Please select from the following:<font color="#FFFFFF">


<center>
<P>
<a href="http://www.strathcona.vic.edu.au/"><img src="buttons/home.gif"></a><a href="invite.html"><img src="buttons/contact.gif"></a><a href="leaders.html"><img src="buttons/leaders.gif"></a><a href="limits.html"><img src="buttons/limits.gif"></a><br>
<a href="potential.html"><img src="buttons/potential.gif"></a><a href="strategies.html"><img src="buttons/strategies.gif"></a><a href="tradition.html"><img src="buttons/tradition.gif"></a><a href="values.html"><img src="buttons/values.gif"></a>
</center>
<P>
