<head>
<title>Development - School and Vision</title>
<BODY BACKGROUND="back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<img src="title.gif">
<P>
<center>
<img src="tc.gif"><br>
<h2 align=left><font color="#FFFF80">Our School</font></h2>
</center>
<p align=center><font color="#FFFFFF"><em><strong>Seventy years ago, Mrs Livingstone and Miss Hughes established Strathcona -<br>
&quot;a school of the highest quality&quot;. That description remains true today.</strong></em></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The quality of our school can be seen in its students, who are the heart of the school. The school's 
value system recognises the individual worth of each person. It is our belief that we can most 
effectively affirm this in a school of the present size.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Education is a life-long process involving meaningful and caring relationships, scholarship, career 
and personal fulfilment. In that process, physical amenities, curricula and programmes are 
important, but their real value lies in the capacity to enhance the opportunities and achievements of 
all girls at Strathcona.</font></p>

<h2><font color="#FFFF00">Our Commitment</font></h2> <p><font
color="#FFFF00"></font>&nbsp;</h1> <p><font color="#FFFFFF"><I><B><center>As ongoing
funding from governments is uncertain, financial independence is crucial to
the future of Strathcona. High standards  can be maintained only when we
all commit ourselves to supporting our school.</font></I></B></center></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF">Contributions may be made in the following ways:</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">1. <strong>Cash Gifts</strong></font></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF">THE STRATHCONA BUILDING &amp; MAINTENANCE FUND</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">This fund provides for the maintenance and
refurbishment of existing buildings and for the construction of new
facilities.  Donations to the Strathcona Building and Maintenance Fund are
<strong>fully tax deductible</strong>.</font></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF">LIBRARY FUND</font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">Gifts to
this fund are directed towards the purchase of books, periodicals,
audio-visual and library equipment. Donations to  this fund are also
<strong>fully tax deductible</strong>.</font></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF"><strong><a href="bequests.html">2. Bequests</A></strong></font></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF">Bequests are a most effective way of providing benefits for
future Strathcona students. Assets left by a will may be either a  share of
an estate, an amount of money, items of personal property, real estate or
the residual value of an annuity.</font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">3.
<strong>Deferred Giving</strong></font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">An
insurance policy (on life or on maturity) is an excellent way of making a
<strong>tax deductible gift</strong> to the school.</font></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF">4.<strong>Assignment of Right of Income</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">This allows income from either capital, shares or
real estate to be donated for a nominated period while retaining ownership
of  these assets. The capital invested <strong>does not attract
tax</strong> normally associated with income from interest.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">5. <strong>Gifts of Assets or
Property</strong></font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">There are many
practical and worthwhile gifts, e.g. real estate, shares in public
companies, personal effects like jewellery and  works of art, collectables,
furniture, motor cars, etc.</font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">6.
<strong>Annual Giving</strong></font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">This
involves a commitment of regular annual donations, perhaps to a specially
designated project, e.g. Music, Sport,  Computers or Languages.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">7. <strong>Friends of Tay
Creggan</strong></font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">Donations in support
of Tay Creggan are <strong>tax deductible </strong>when made payable to The
Strathcona Building and Maintenance  Fund.</font></p> <p><font
color="#FFFFFF"></font>&nbsp;</p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">We ask that each
member of the Strathcona family consider the ways in which they can assist
us to realise our vision</font></p> <p><font color="#FFFFFF">For further
details, please contact the Director of Development, Jack Moshakis, on (03)
9836 1611.</font></p>


<h2><font color="#FFFF80">Our Vision</font></h2>
<p align=center><font color="#FFFFFF"><em><strong>Our vision for the 90's and beyond is to pursue a policy of dynamic excellence in the 
education of the whole person within a distinctively Christian framework.</strong></em></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">In recent years, advances in educational technology have been unprecedented, sporting and 
co-curricular activities have diversified, and curricular offerings have increased. Whilst being proud 
of our beautiful grounds and fine facilities, we recognise the challenge to provide resources of the 
highest calibre to support all the educational programmes at Strathcona.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Four major areas of development have been identified by the School Council, to take us to the year 
2000.</font></p><P> <B><I> Please select the headings below for additional information.</I></B><P>
<h3><font color="#FFFFFF"><a href="humanit.html">1. Humanities Centre</a></font></h3>
<blockquote>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">This features an exciting and comprehensive learning centre incorporating a 130 person lecture 
theatre, a chapel, an archive room, administrative facilities, technologically equipped classrooms 
and a rooftop garden. The Humanities Centre was completed in 1994.</font> </blockquote></p>
<h3><font color="#FFFFFF"><a href="sci.html">2.	Science &amp; Technology Centre</a></font></h3>
<blockquote>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Changes in emphasis and in teaching methodology require access to more 
sophisticated equipment. Modern, attractive and functional laboratories are 
essential in retaining and encouraging a love of science and mathematics. In recognition of this, the school is currently constructing a new $2 million facility which will be opened mid 1997. </font></p>
</blockquote>
<h3><font color="#FFFFFF"><a href="boat.html">3.	Boating Facilities</a></font></h3>
<blockquote>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Strathcona is fortunate in being one of a few schools in Australia with a river 
frontage. A jetty is being built at Tay Creggan so that our girls can participate in a 
broader range of physical and recreational activities, including rowing.</font></blockquote></p>
<p>
<h3><font color="#FFFFFF">4.	Tay Creggan Restoration</font></h3>
<blockquote>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">This magnificent property requires major plumbing work, extensive work on the garden terraces and renewed furnishings. The aim is to restore the buildings and gardens during this decade.  
<P>
<center>
<hr><P>
