<html>
<title>Strathcona - Nutrition</title>
<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<center>
<img src="icons/nutrition.gif">
</center>
<P>
<hr>
<P><h2>Index</h2>
<dl>
<dt><b><i>Please choose from the following sections:</b>
<dd><a href="#diet">Diet, Health and Nutrition</a><br>
<dd><a href="#eating">Eating Disorders</a><br>
<dd><a href="#recipes">Recipes and Cooking</a><br>
</dl>
<P><hr>
</i>
<dl>
<a name="diet"</a>
<dt><h4>Diet, Nutrition and Health</h4>
<dd><a href="http://www.ag.uiuc.edu/~food-lab/nat/mainnat.html">Nutrition Analysis Tool</a> allows you to analyse the nutrition content of common foods.
<dd><a href="gopher://zeus.esusda.gov:70/11/feds/fda">The American Food and Drug Administration</a>  contains a wide range of information on the impact of diet and nutrition on health and development.  This resource also contains information on food and drug labeling.
<dd><a href="http://vm.cfsan.fda.gov/list.html">The US Federal Food and Drug Administration Center for Food Safety and Applied Nutrition</a> provides information on topics including: food additives, food labelling, peticides and chemicals, seafood, women,s health, biotechnology and plant toxins, milk safety information, cosmetics and foodborne illnesses.  A section on educational resources is also included.
<dd><a href="http://web.bu.edu/COHIS/nutrition/nutrisrc.htm">HealthScource: Diet and Nutrition</a> by Ami Levin.  This is a very good resource on a wide range of diet related issues.  Topics covered include: caffeine, carbohydrates, exercise, facts of fat, fast food, food additives, food allergies, food labelling and nutritional information, recipies and glossaries and references.  Sections on vegetarian diets, vitamins, minerals and nutrients, weight and diet, eating disorders (bulimia and anorexia), and links to other sites make this a valuable starting place for searching the web.
<dd><a href="http://www.usatoday.com/life/health/lh99.htm">USA Today - Health Index</a>  This is a general listing of news items covered by USA Today on the topic of health.  Included in this section is a substantial resource on diet and nutrition.
<dd><a href="http://ericir.syr.edu/Projects/Newton/10/lessons/DietNut.html">Newton's Apple</a> - Diet and Nutrition.  This resource provides information on diet and nutrition including information on: proteins, fats, carbohydrates and calories.  Included is a worksheet designed for students as well as links to other sites containing information on this topic.
<dd><a href="http://alpha.genebee.msu.su/diet/">Diet and Nutrition in Aging</a> This site provides information about the impact of diet on aging.  It provides an excellent discussion on the impact of vitamins and minerals on the aging process.
<dd><a href="http://deja-vu.oldiron.cornell.edu/~jabbo/faq.html">A Compilation of Frequently Asked Questions</a> from the newsgroup Sci.Med.Nutrition.  Although the information in this section is a little hard to find it does contains some excellent facts and discussions.  This introduction page contains links to other pages covering information on, lifestyle and sports nutrition.

<dd><a href="http://www.nalusda.gov/fnic/"><b>Food and Nutrition Information Center</a> is an excellent resource covering a wide range of food and health related issues.  Included are sections on:  dietary guidelines, healthy eating index, food service management, food labeling,  foodborne illness education, educational materials and links to other Internet resources.


<dd><a href="http://ificinfo.health.org/"><b>International Food Information Council</b>
</a>"Anyone interested in food issues" can find a pantry full of info here. Parents who need help with their kids' eating habits, consumers worried about the effects of aspartame, reporters researching pesticides and teachers looking for food safety curriculum materials are just a sampling of the questioners served at this site.
<dd><a href="http://www.alaska.net/~tne/"><b>The Nutrition Expert</b>
</a>
A group of registered dietitians provides information about weight loss, cholesterol, sports nutrition, diabetes control and health  food here. The site also includes an eating disorders bibliography and links to other Internet sites containing information on nutrition and eating disorders. 
<dd><a href="http://deja-vu.oldiron.cornell.edu/~jabbo"><b>The Nutrition Pages</b>
</a>
<dd>The Nutrition Pages contains a collection of  pages on nutrition and health. Includes a  collection of articles and  Frequently Asked Questions section covering basic definitions, lifestyle and sports nutrition. This iste also includes links to other Internet resources.

<dd><a href="http://envirolink.org/arrs/VRG/home.html"><b>Vegetarian Resource Group</b>
</a>
 Vegetarianism and animal rights are the focus of the  Vegetarian Resource Group home page. Resources include  journals, nutrition information, recipes, travel guides and  links. 
<a name="eating"</a>
<dt><h4>Eating Disorders</h4>
<dd><a href="http://www.psyc.nott.ac.uk/~les/eat.htm">Eating Disorders - Index</a>.  This is an index of Internet resources related to the topic of eating disorders.  This list is updated regularly.
<dd><a href="http://www.sc.edu/library/science/eating.html">Eating Disorders Pathfinder - Science Library HomePage</a>.  This pathfinder is designed to get you started on finding research materials on all apects of eating disorders.  This site lists a number of US publications and books on this topic that may not be available in Australia, however, there is a section on Internet resources related to eating disorders.
<dd><a href="http://www.healthtouch.com/level1/leaflets/102952/anad003.htm">Eating Disorder - Definitions</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.healthtouch.com/level1/leaflets/102952/anad004.htm">HealthTouch - Health Information</a> What to do if you have an eating disorder.
<dd><a href="http://www.healthtouch.com/level1/leaflets/102952/102952.htm">HealthTouch - Health Information</a> Eating Disorders.  This site contains information on: eating disorder definitions, treating eating disorders, eating disorder studies and the dangers of dieting and diet products.
<dd><a href="http://qlink.queensu.ca/~4map/files/moreinfo.htm">Information on Eating Disorders</a> provided by the American Anorexia Nervosa and Bumimia Association.  Contents: warning signs, factors contributing to eating disorders, the biology of eating disorders, treatments and diagnosis.
<dd><a href="http://bertha.chattanooga.net/news/healthwatch/hw9.html">Healthwatch - Athletes and eating Disorders</a> 
<a name="recipes"</a>
<dt><h4>Recipes and Cooking</h4>
<dd><a href="http://english-server.hss.cmu.edu/Recipes.html"><b>CMU Students' Recipes Folder</b>
</a> 


</dl>
<p>
<center>
<hr><p>
<i><b>If you are aware of addition resources related to this topic suitable for students aged between 10 and 16 years of age, please notify the:  <br>
<a href ="mailto:kperkins@hub.strathcona.vic.edu.au">System Administrator </a>
</center>
</body>
