<title> Strathcona Baptist Girls Grammar School - Computers</title>
<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<center>
<h1>Computers and Technology</h1>
</center>
<br><a href="http://www.com.au/apc/">Australian Personal Computer</a> magazine offers articles, news and reviews on computers and related topics.
<br><a href="http://www.dgr.com/">Bottom Line Online</a>  This is a resource for Apple Macintosh users.
<br><a href="http://www.bcs.org.uk/">British Computer Society</a>  offers information about computing, international conferences and general computer news.  Includes a section on education.
<br><a href="http://www.buds.co.uk/">BUDS Home Page</a>Hewlett-Packard technical support.
<br><a href="http://techweb.cmp.com/techweb/docs/list-o-pubs.html">CMP Publications</a>
<br><a href="http://www.ccurrents.com/cc/">Computer Currents Interactive</a>
<br><a href="http://www.complife.ziff.com/~complife/">Computer Life Online</a>
<br><a href="http://gpg.com/cnme/">Computer News Middle East </a>
<br><a href="http://www.tcp.ca/">The Computer Paper </a> Canadian computer  magazine providing small computer news and reviews.
<br><a href="http://techweb.cmp.com/techweb/crn/current/default.html">Computer Reseller News</a>
<br><a href="http://techweb.cmp.com/techweb/crw/current/default.html">Computer Retail Week
</a> Computer news, employment and research resources.
<br><a href="http://info.acm.org/crossroads/index.html">The Crossroads Homepage</a>  The student magazine of the Association for Computing Machinery.
<br><a href="http://www.cwi.nl/">Home Page of CWI</a>  CWI is a Dutch research institute for mathermatics and computer science.
<br><a href="http://zoomer.netcarta.com/stacks/news/www.hotwired.com.wmp">Hotwired </a>  The major online computer and World Wide Web magazine
<br><a href="http://www.atom.co.jp/MACLIFE/index-e.html">Maclife</a>  A Japanese monthly magazine covering the latest new on developments in technology.
<br><a href="http://www.cris.com/~milewski/magnet.html">MagNet</a>  Magnet is a listing of online computer magazines and resources.
<br><a href="http://awa.com/nct">NCT Web Magazine</a> features news, reviews and items of interest to people who are developing their own web pages.
