<html>
<title> Strathcona Baptist Girls Grammar School</title>

<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">

<center>
<img src="icons/olympic.gif">
</center>
<P>
<dl>

<P>
<DT><h3>ATLANTA NEWS and INFORMATION</H3>
<dt><h4>Olympic News</h4>
<dd><a href="http://results.atlanta.olympic.org/">Olympic Results</a> inlcuding medals standings, recent results, recent medals and search for athletes.
<dd><a href="http://sports.eb.com">Encyclopedia Britannica</a> sporting record - The Olympic Games
<dt> <h4>Australia at the Atlanta Games</h4>
<dd><a href="http://www.olympics.ni.com.au/">News Interactives Olympics '96</a>.  News Limited's Official Olympic Handbook includes photos and profiles of the whole Australian Olympic team.
<dd><a href="http://www.atlanta.fairfax.com.au">Australia at the Atlanta Olympics</a>.  This is an excellent resource covering the latest results, Australia's progress and team member profiles.

<dd><a href="http://www.ausport.gov.au/home.html">Australian Sports Commission Home Page</a> This site offers considerable information on the Australian Olympic team.
<dd><a href="http://www.ausport.gov.au/olymenu.html"><b>Australian Sports Commission </b></a>  Olympic resource.  Featuring information on both the modern and ancient Olympics.  Special topics include a detailled look at Australia's history of Olympic involvement.

<dt><h3>The Modern Olympics</h3>

<dd><a href="http://www.atlantagames.com/index.htm"><b>Atlanta Games</b></a>  This is an unofficial Olympic Games server but it does offer some interesting information.

<dd><a href="http://www.mindspring.com/~prog400/atlanta.html"><b>Atlanta Quick Olympics Guide</b></a>
  This guide to Atlanta contains information for visitors headed for the Olympics in 1996, including housing, tickets, maps, a calendar and details about the sports. Includes additional links to other Olympic sites and corporate sponsors.
<dd><a href="http://www.sportsnetusa.com/olympics/"><b>Authentic Olympic Games Collection</b></a>  This site provides information about products and promotions associated with the Olympics.  It also has some interesting historical information.
<dd><a href="http://www.com-stock.com/dave"><b>It's Atlanta! - The Olympic Web Page</b></a>  This is an excellent guide to the Olympics.  This site includes information about Atlanta, the events and even links to associated  organizations home pages.
<dd><a href="http://167.8.29.13/olympics/oly.htm"><b>Latest Olympic News</b></a>  USA Today provides a wealth of information through this server including detailled event information and results.
<dd><a href="http://www.atlanta.olympic.org/"><b>1996 Centennial Olympic Games Home Page</b></a>
  Visitors to the official site for the 1996 Atlanta Committee for the  Olympic Games will find Olympic sports and  venues, ticket information, official products, travel  information and the official program of the 1996 Summer  Olympics.
<dd><a href="http://www.olympic.org/"><b>The Olympic Movement</a></b>  The International Olympic Committee service provides the latest press releases about the IOC and historical information about the Olympic movement.
<dd><a href="http://www.sydney.olympic.org/"><b>Sydney, Australia Olympics</b></a> server covers a wide range of issues and topics concerning the 2000 Olympics.  This site is growing rapidly as the games approach.

<dt><h3>The Ancient Olympics</h3><P>


<dd><a href="http://www.pages-plus.com/Olympic/">HELLAS' Olympic Page</a></b> This resource focuses on the history of the Olympic Flame and its role in both the ancient and modern Olympics.
<dd><a href="http://www.ausport.gov.au/anc.html">The history of the Ancient Olympics</a></b>  This is a section of the information provided by the Australian Sports Commision about the Olympic Games.  This is a text resource of considerable depth.
<dd><a href="http://www.wam.umd.edu/~cyprus/olympic.html">The Spirit of Ancient Olympics</a></b>  This resource looks at the role Cyprus played in the Ancient Olympics.
<dd><a href="http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/olympic/">Olympic Virtual Museum</a></b>  This is an outstanding resource covering a wide range of issues and topics on the Ancient Olympics.  Included is a virtual museum where the visitor can enter a selection of rooms to view the exhibits.
<dd><a href="http://www.ee.surrey.ac.uk/Societies/hellsoc/hellas/olympic.html">Olympia Project</a></b> The Spirit of the Ancient Olympics.  This site focuses on the Hellenic heritage of the Ancient Olympics.



</body>
</html>
