<html>

<head>
<title>Stretching the Limits</title>
<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<img src="icons/commitment.gif">
<center>

<P><img src="icons/jump.gif"><P><font color="#FFFF00"><em><B><I>Strathcona treats me as an individual, rather than just another student.</em></font></B></I></center>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Stretching the Limits</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Maximum participation, enjoyment and the realisation of potential are the key aims of sport at Strathcona, and our excellent 
facilities ensure that students are provided with optimum opportunity to achieve them. Participation is encouraged for its 
contribution to self-esteem, confidence, social interaction and the development of a healthy lifestyle.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>Sport</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The sporting program at Form, House and Inter-school levels caters for a wide spectrum of talents and interests. Sports 
offered include athletics, badminton, basketball, cricket, cross-country, diving, hockey, netball, rhythmic gymnastics, 
lifesaving, softball, swimming, tennis and volleyball. Strathcona is also represented in downhill and freestyle skiing and by 
rowing teams.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>Outdoor Activities</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Outdoor experiences are introduced in Year 3 and offered subsequently in an exciting and varied program designed to match 
students' increasing abilities. These include camps, which are allied to aspects of the curriculum and complementary to them.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The Duke of Edinburgh program, bushwalking, canoeing, rafting, cross-country skiing, initiative and navigation activities and 
abseiling encourage girls to gain a greater understanding of themselves and an appreciation of the outdoors.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Clubs, such as the SPAM outdoor adventure club, are popular with students in Years 10 to 12 who thrive on the challenges 
offered during weekends and holidays. Horseriding, ski camps and the Kakadu Safari are always enthusiastically patronised.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>


<center>
<P>
<HR><P>
<a href="http://www.strathcona.vic.edu.au/"><img src="buttons/home.gif"></a><a href="invite.html"><img src="buttons/contact.gif"></a><a href="leaders.html"><img src="buttons/leaders.gif"></a><a href="limits.html"><img src="buttons/limits.gif"></a><br>
