<html>

<head>
<title>Realisation of Potential</title>
<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<img src="icons/potential.gif">
<center>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#0000FF">

<h3><font color="#FFFF00"><em>Education at Strathcona is centred on, and celebrates, the uniqueness of the individual.</em></font></h3>
<P><img src="icons/music.gif"><P>
</center>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">VCE and Beyond</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Strathcona girls have consistently achieved excellent results. Their outstanding performances in the Victorian Certificate of 
Education reflect the commitment, enthusiasm and hard work of both students and their teachers. A 100% pass rate has been 
repeatedly achieved, with more than 99% of students in recent years continuing on to higher study.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Recent graduates have been awarded Premier's Awards, Australian Students Prizes (given by the Prime Minister to students 
with the highest results in Australia) and major engineering prizes. This continues a long tradition of excellence.</font></p>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Enhancing the Education Experience</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">In keeping with Strathcona's philosophy of education being an experience designed to prepare the individual for the future in 
all facets of life, our co-curricular program is rich in its scope.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>Debating and Public Speaking</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">From Year 1, speech lessons are available. Participation of students in assemblies, concerts and competitions is encouraged, 
and debating is held at both Inter-House and Inter-School levels.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>Drama and Dance</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Drama and Dance is available in many forms in the co-curricular program. Inter-house Drama productions are held twice 
yearly. They are written and produced by senior students and include girls from Year 7 upwards. The annual play and musical 
are highly professional productions.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>Music</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Strathcona has a strong instrumental and choral tradition. From Year 3, when violin is part of the core curriculum, every 
student is offered an opportunity to participate in the broad and varied program. A wide range of groups - from the large 
orchestras, bands, ensembles and choirs to smaller, more intimate quartets, trios, madrigals and instrumental ensembles - 
ensures that girls acquire the skills needed to express their creativity while performing in public with assurance and poise.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The Composer Club offers girls in Years 9 to 12 an international forum to compose and communicate world-wide with other 
students using the latest music technology.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>Cultural</strong></font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Global perspective is increased through student exchange programs with sister schools in New Zealand, Asia and Europe.</font></p>


<center>
<P>
<HR><P>
<a href="http://www.strathcona.vic.edu.au/"><img src="buttons/home.gif"></a><a href="invite.html"><img src="buttons/contact.gif"></a><a href="leaders.html"><img src="buttons/leaders.gif"></a><a href="limits.html"><img src="buttons/limits.gif"></a><br>
