<html>

<head>
<title>Innovative Learning Strategies</title>

</head>


<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<img src="icons/learning.gif">
<body bgcolor="#0000FF">
<center><I><B>
<font color="#FFFF00"><em>Learning takes on many innovative forms at Strathcona, such as the use of interactive 
multimedia.</em></font></center></i></b>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">A Curriculum Focused on Excellence</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">We know that students learn best when programs cater for their individual needs and talents. Strathcona's curriculum 
emphasises a rich and diverse range of learning strategies so that our students become adaptable, multi-skilled and 
independent. It encourages students to think critically and creatively, to develop global awareness and to work co-operatively 
to establish the skills needed for life-long learning. From the earliest years through to graduation, girls are encouraged to strive 
for excellence and to plan for the future.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">In Mellor House, the core curriculum is extensive with major emphasis on literacy and numeracy. &quot;Hands on&quot; science activities 
foster a lasting enthusiasm for science, and our LOTE program, which begins at Prep, encourages awareness of other cultures 
including French, Italian and Korean.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The Middle School curriculum is designed so that subject specialisation is deferred as long as possible. All girls study Art, 
Christian Education, Drama, English, French, History, Geography, Mathematics, Music, Physical Education, Science, 
Technology and Life Skills. Students may also select Italian or Korean in Year 8. There are extension and special assistance 
programs and a unique FOCUS program. These challenge and support students at either end of the learning scale.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">In Year 9, students need to develop independence and explore ideas, and new subjects such as Design using computers, 
Music Technology and Horticulture are introduced. General studies, which is held on one day each week, has an international 
reputation for its innovative learning strategies, including the development of multimedia authoring. The skills acquired during 
this unique experience provide a stimulating basis for senior years.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">In Years 10 to 12, girls begin their preparation for VCE and life beyond school. Over 10 VCE units are offered: all Year 10 
girls take at least one, many Year 11 girls take units 3 and 4 and there are opportunities to study first year university 
enhancement subjects in Year 12.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The academic program is supported by careers counselling, visiting speakers and seminars and an excellent career 
planning/work experience program.</font></p>


<center>
<P>
<HR><P>
<a href="http://www.strathcona.vic.edu.au/"><img src="buttons/home.gif"></a><a href="invite.html"><img src="buttons/contact.gif"></a><a href="leaders.html"><img src="buttons/leaders.gif"></a><a href="limits.html"><img src="buttons/limits.gif"></a><br>
