<html>

<head>
<title>Tradition and Change</title>

</head>


<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<img src="icons/tradition.gif">
<center>

<B><I><font color="#FFFF00"><em>Proud of its past, and active in embracing the future, Strathcona offers students the best of both 
worlds.</em></font></i></b></center>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">There are modern classrooms, fully equipped science, technology and language laboratories, a light-filled creative arts centre 
with specialist studios which have computers and an excellent gallery for display of student work. State-of-the-art computer 
technology has helped to establish the school's reputation for innovation in the areas of multimedia and communications, and 
three information centres combine library, computer and audio visual facilities.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">An indoor physical education centre incorporating a gymnasium with full-size basketball court and a heated swimming pool is 
used throughout the year. Sports facilities on each campus include an oval and netball, tennis and basketball courts. An 
adventure playground in the Junior School, together with specialist outdoor areas for preparatory children, caters for those 
beginning school.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The situation of the Junior School within the main campus allows even our youngest the opportunity to make extensive use of 
all these outstanding facilities.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">In recognition of the importance of Year 9 as a time of growth, exploration and developing autonomy, Strathcona's Year 9 
students attend a separate campus, Tay Creggan in Hawthorn.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Tay Creggan, on the banks of the Yarra River, is a marvellous blend of tradition and change. It features beautiful historic 
buildings set in extensive grounds which are classified by the Australian Heritage Commission. Its elegant hall has an open 
fireplace, which provides a welcoming place for girls to gather.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">The grounds at the main school and the magnificent Tay Creggan campus both feature tranquil gardens.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Mellor House, Strathcona's Junior School, offers a warm, friendly and purposeful environment for students from 
Pre-Preparatory to Year 6. Small class sizes, individual attention and opportunities for each person to participate in all aspects 
of the program are distinctive features of our school. After school care is provided until 6 p.m. on weekdays, and there are 
holiday programs.</font></p>


<center>
<P>
