<html>

<head>
<title>Bequests</title>
</head>

<BODY BACKGROUND="back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#ffffff" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<h1><font color="#FFFF00">THE STRATHCONA BEQUEST 
PROGRAMME</font></h1>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00"><em>Benefiting the School by your Will</em></font></h3>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">What is a Bequest?</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">A Bequest is a gift in a Will in which the person making the Will leaves an asset to a charity, an 
individual or an organisation like the Strathcona Foundation.</font></p>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Why Bequests?</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">All independent schools are seeking ways of raising money to maintain and improve their financial 
independence in the face of declining and uncertain Government support. In Australia, the United 
States of America and the United Kingdom, some 80% of private funding to independent schools 
comes from Bequests. Bequests also provide a very effective way for people to support Strathcona 
in a way in which they cannot do so from their present income.</font></p>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Bequests to the Strathcona Foundation</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">By making a Bequest to the Foundation, rather than the School, the money is managed so that 
there will be little or no effect on government funding. In addition, Bequests to the Foundation are 
currently free from Federal and State probate and gift duty.</font></p>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Bequest Advisory Service</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">It is important that professional and legal advice is taken regarding the establishment of any benefit 
for Strathcona, particularly where a Will maker would prefer to leave real estate or other assets to 
the School. Strathcona is pleased to offer a free, confidential, no obligation advisory service. In 
addition, our Bequest Service can make or amend Wills without charge where Strathcona is to be 
made a beneficiary.</font></p>
<h3><font color="#FFFF00">Strathcona's Legacy and the Future</font></h3>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">The memories that former students have of Strathcona are inevitably linked with an era of the 
School's history, fellow students, a Principal or staff.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">It is the role of the Foundation to ensure that the School continues to thrive as a vibrant educational 
institution. It is committed to providing opportunities to girls through a reasonable fee structure 
which keeps the school as accessible as possible. To maintain our fine traditions and to ensure the 
future financial independence of our School, the Foundation is seeking the support of the 
Strathcona Community.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">While many people are able to support Strathcona during their lifetime, others may find it easier to 
support the School through their Will.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">Should you wish to remember Strathcona in your Will, we suggest you consider the many ways in 
which a Bequest can be made:</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">1. A gift of a specific sum of money.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">2. A gift of real estate.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">3. A percentage of your estate.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">4. A gift of assets including shares, life insurance policy, jewellery, works of art, antiques and other 
collectables.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">5. Establishment of a scholarship, bursary or prize.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">6. Gifts for the School can be either for the general purposes of the School or for specifically 
nominated projects, e.g. buildings, music, science, the arts, information technology or professional 
development for staff.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00"></font>&nbsp;</p>

<P>
<center>
