<title> Strathcona - Humanities</title>

<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<center>

<img src="icons/humanities.gif">
</center>

<P><hr><p>
<h3>Index</h3>
<P>The following sub-topics are referenced:
<dl>
<dd><a href="#australia">Australia</a>
<dd><a href="#antarctica">Antarctica</a>
<dd><a href="civil.html">American Civil War</a>
<dd><a href="disasters.html">Natural Disasters</a>
<dd><a href="#environment">The Environment</a>
<dd><a href="#country">International Studies</a>

<P><hr><P>
<h3><a name="australia">Australia</a></h3>
<DD><A HREF = "http://life.anu.edu.au:80/weather.html">Global Weather Satelite Images and  Forecasts</A> This selection also includes <B><I>EARTH QUAKE REPORTS</I></B>, a selection of <B><I>WORLD MAPS</I></B> and <B><I>CLIMATIC INFORMATION</I></B>.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.parks.tas.gov.au/environment/climate/climate.html">Tasmanian Climate</A> Information regarding Tasmania's climate with links to<B> <I> DAILY FORECASTS </I></B>and<B><I> WEATHER ALERTS</I>.</B>
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.parks.tas.gov.au/tpws.html">Tasmanian Parks and Wildlife Service</A> information about Tasmanian Fauna and Flora.
<DD><A HREF = "http://life.anu.edu.au/education/australia.html">Guide To Australia</A> This service includes information on; Australian Geography, World Maps, Australian Vegetation, Tourism and Travel, The Australian Constitution, other Australian and overseas World Wide Web sites, Telecom, Governor Lachlan Macquarie, and airline timetables.
<a name="antarctica"></a>
<DT><H3>Antarctica</H3>

<DD><A HREF = "http://www.deakin.edu.au/edu/MSEE/GENII/NSPT/NSPThomePage.html">The South Polar Times</A> from Deakin University.  Is an outstanding resource covering Australia's activities in Antarctica.  The South Polar Times is produced in Antarctica and covers topics including: polar exploration, weather, lessons and ideas and climatic monitoring.  You may also subscribe to a discussion group if you have access to email.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.deakin.edu.au/edu/MSEE/GENII/NSPT/HistSPExpl.html">A History of Antarctic Exploration</A> from Deakin University. (Part of the Polar Times resource).
<DD><A HREF = "http://icair.iac.org.nz/">Antarctic Online</A> This service offers a vaste amount of information on all aspects of Antarctica; including treaties, international claims, climate and wildlife.
<DD><A HREF = "http://quest.arc.nasa.gov/livefrom/livefrom.html">NASA's Live From Antarctica</A>  This is an outstanding resource on Antarctica designed for students and teachers.


<dd><A HREF="http://www.awi-bremerhaven.de/">Alfred Wegener
Institute</A>, the German national centre for Polar and
Marine research

<dd><A HREF="http://dilbert.lbl.gov/www/amanda.html">AMANDA</A>, the neutrino telescope project at the South Pole.  This contains complex scientific information but does serve as an example of the type of scientific research being conducted in Antarctica.
<dd><A HREF="gopher://gopher.ssec.wisc.edu/11/amrc.d">Antarctica
Meteorology Research Center</A>.  Composite satellite weather images covering the Southern Hemisphere.  Images are available for downloading.

<dd>
<A HREF="http://www.asa.org/">Antarctic Support Associates</A>  Offers a range of resources and information about Antarctica of varying degrees of complexity including images and written information.
<dd><A HREF="http://orca.iasos.utas.edu.au/WWW/local/antcrc.html">Australian Antarctic Cooperative Research Center</A> Tasmania.  This service is mainly concerned with the impact of climate change on Antarctica.  It offers some excellent information about the roles that the Earth's oceans play in relation to climate and the the way climate change can be measured by studying the ice sheet in Antarctica.
<dd><A HREF="http://newt.phys.unsw.edu.au/~mgb/jacara.html">Australian Working Group for Antarctic Astronomy</A>  This service provides detailled and technical information about Australian programs in austronomy in Antarctica.  Weather satelite and other images are available including wildlife and scenery.
<dd><A HREF="http://www.nerc-bas.ac.uk/">British Antarctic Survey</A>  Includes information on climate, fishing, research stations, ships, upper atmosphere research, marine life and geological information.  A gallery of images are available.
<dd><A HREF="http://www-bprc.mps.ohio-state.edu/">Byrd Polar Research
Center</A> at Ohio State University.  This resource contains a list of informationa available at Ohio University which can be borrowed as well as some weather satelite images of Antarctica and pointers to other Internet information on this subject.
<dd><A HREF="http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/dmsp/dmsp.html">Defense Meteorological Satellite Program (DMSP) Data Archive </A> at NGDC.  Provides satelite images covering dramatic weather events for the entire planet including  Antarctica.
<dd><A HREF="http://www.antcrc.utas.edu.au/iasos.html">Institute of Antarctic and Southern Ocean Studies</A> Tasmania.  This resource goves information about IASOS as well as contact information about people involved in this program.
<dd><A HREF="http://www.crseo.ucsb.edu/lter/lter.html">Long Term Ecological Research</A>  in Antarctica is supported by the National Science Foundation and aims to monitor the changes in the ecology of Antarctica.  Although some of the information contained in this resource is complex it does give an excellent example of the type of scientific research being conducted in this region.
<dd><A HREF="http://barsoom.msss.com/http/ant/intro.html">Malin's
Antarctic Research.</A> Antarctic images by Malin Space Science Systems Inc.  cover the effects of weathering in ice free areas.  This resource contains some excellent images of the effects of weathering in the Antarctic.
<dd><A HREF="http://www.npolar.no">Norsk Polarinstitutt</A> (Polar Institute of Norway).  Provides information about scientific research being conducted in the Arctic and the Antarctic.
<dd><A HREF="http://www.nsf.gov/">NSF WWW server Home Page</A>, including the <A HREF="http://www.nsf.gov/opp/start.htm">Office of Polar Programs</A> which outlines major polar programs being undertaken by the Unites States of America.  This is an excellent resource covering a wide range of topics.
<dd><A HREF="http://hmu1.cs.aukuni.ac.nz/Corca">Orca Research</A> by Ingrid Visser.  This resource contains some excellent images of Antarctic wildlife as well as information relating to studies on the Orca.
<dd><A HREF="gopher://gopher.ucalgary.ca/11/library/polar">Polar Libraries Gopher</A> maintained by Eric Tull, University of Calgary.  This service provides links to libraries that have information about the Arctic and the Antarctic.  

<dd><A HREF="http://www.puk.ac.za/fskdocs/omg/omg_antE.html">South African National Antarctic Research Program</A>  home page (English).  This resource offers information about South Africa's Antarctic program and includes information and images.
<a name="environment"</a>
<DT><H3><img src="icons/environ.gif">The Environment</H3>
<DD><A HREF = "http://kaos.erin.gov.au:80/erin.html">The Environmental Information Resources Network</A> offers information about the
Austaliain environment.  Includes data on  the: air, land and water, humans and the environment, the sea,
the state of the environment and the sea.  A keyword search option is available.  An excellent section on the
Greenhouse effect is available.
<dt><h4>Great Barrier Reef</h4>
<dd><a href="http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/">Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority</a>
<a name="country"></a>
<dd><a href="http://www.cco.caltech.edu/~salmon/wh-gbreef.html">Great Barrier Reef</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.uni-stuttgart.de/UNIuser/igps/edu/JRP/JRP_english1.html">Jurassic Reef Park</a>

<DT><H3><img src="icons/globe.gif">International Studies</H3>
<dd><A HREF="http://www.odci.gov/cia/publications/95fact/index.html">CIA World Fact Book 1995</a>.  This is an excellent resource covering political, social, economic and environmental information on all countries.  This site also contains world maps and other CIA publications.
<DD><A HREF = "http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVL-AsianStudies.html">Asia</A>.  This server offers information abut Asia and Asian Studies.
<DD><A HREF="korea.html">Korea</a>.  A list of Internet information resources on North and South Korea.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.fleethouse.com/fhcanada/fhc_expl.htm">Canada</A>.  This server offers information about Canada, covering all regions.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.es.clemson.edu/~nandu/india.html">India</A>.  This server offers information about India.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.rcp.net..pe/rcp.html">Peru</A>.  Information of both a cultural and tourist nature on the South American  nation of Peru.
<DD><A HREF = "/Japan/home.htm">Japan</A>  This  offers information about most aspects of the study of Japan; including, geography, history, technology, culture and society.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.ege.edu.tr/Turkiye/">Turkey</A> This server offers information on many aspects of Turkey, including images of places within the country.
<DD><A HREF = "http://www.het.brown.edu:80/hungerweb/">Famine, Hunger and the Developing World</A>,  covering information dealing with starvation and famine.  This server includes an interactive quiz dealing with this topic.
</DL>
</DOC>
