<title> Strathcona - Korea</title>
<body>
<BODY BACKGROUND="icons/back.gif" BGCOLOUR="#000000" VLINK="#8888ff" TEXT="#f5f50c" LINK="#ffffff" ALINK="#ff8888">
<center>
<img src="icons/korea.gif">

</center>
<dl>
<P>
<dt><I>NOTE: Korean World Wide Web servers tend to be slow due to the speed of the Internet link into that country.  Any resource with an address ending with kr will take some time to load.</I><P>
<dd><a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional/Countries/Korea__South/">Yahoo - Korean resources</a> offers a searchable database of information on South Korea.
<dd><a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Regional/Countries/Korea__North/">Yahoo - Korean resources</a> offers a searchable database of information on North Korea.
<dd><a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Politics/Regional/Countries/Korea__South/">Yahoo - Korean resources</a> offers a searchable database of information on the political situation in both North and South Korea.
<dd><a href="http://radioworks.cbc.ca/radio/programs/current/ideas/ideasnk.html">North Korea</a> provided by the IDEAS program in Canada.
<dd><a href="http://newnet.kii.go.kr/">Korean World Wide Web Servers.</a>  This is a list that includes: Korean Universities, government agencies, organizations (mainly cultural) and major corporations.
<dd><a href="http://emailhost.ait.ac.th/Asia/infokr.html">Country Information - Korea</a>  This resource includes: travel, human rights, business, the aerospace industry, World Bank projects and general cultural, social and geograpical information on Korea.
<dd><a href="http://www.worldwide.edu/ci/korea/../south_korea/fsouth_korea.html">South Korean Schools</a>  This is a list of South Korean schools compiled by the WorldWide Classroom.  Contact names and mail addresses are supplied, Email addresses and WWW information is NOT listed.
<dd><a href="http://cair.kaist.ac.kr/korea/index.html">The Republic of  Korea</a> Information provided includes: Korea at a glance, what to do, what to see and touring information.
<dd><a href="http://www.ncl.ac.uk/~n5820074/korea.html">Korean Culture Page</a> (UK).  This is an excellent resource covering many areas of South Korea and South Korean Culture.  

<dt><h2>Korean News Services</h2>
<dd><a href="http://www.joongang.co.kr/">JoongAng Daily News</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.ked.co.kr/">Korea Economic Daily</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.nowcom.co.kr/hankook.html">Korea Times</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.seoul.co.kr/">Seoul Daily News</a>
<dd><a href="http://news.hani.co.kr/">Hangyore 21</a> (weekly)
<dd><a href="http://zec.three.co.kr/">Korea Herald News</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.kimsoft.com/korea.htm">Korea WebWeekly</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.m2000.co.kr/">M2000/Taego daily News</a>
<dd><a href="http://iwww.islandtel.com/newsbytes/">Newsbytes Pacifica</a>
