<title>Getting Started with Virtual Susanville</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h1>Getting Started with Virtual Susanville</h1>
<p>Both a standard web browser interface, as well as a 3D interface are provided to browse content 
on <a href="/index.html">www.Susanville.com</a>. Virtual Susanville refers to the 3D browsing capabilities using VRML 
(Virtual Reality Markup Language). If you'd like to use the 3D interface, follow Steps 1 and 2 below, if not, <a href="/index.html">click here</a>. </p>
<h2>Step 1 - Installing a VRML web browser</h2>
<p>The VRML Repository maintains an <a href="http://www.sdsc.edu/vrml/browsers.html">archive of VRML web browsers</a>. Download and install the 
browser of your choice. Any of these browsers will work. </p>
<h2>Step 2 - Enter the Virtual Susanville 'world'</h2>
<p>Launch the VRML browser by clicking the following link: <a href="/susanvil.wrl">Virtual Susanville</a>. </p>
<p align=center><a href="mailto:cannon@susanville.com">Questions &amp; Comments</a>.
<p align=center><a href="http://www.susanville.com"><img src="./graphics/stest.gif" border=0 align=bottom width=54 height=54></a></p>
</body>

