<h3><u>Executive Management Biographies</u></h3>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="5">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em>John C. Wheeler, President and CEO <br>
        <br>
        E-mail address: </em><a href="mailto:jcw@copper-mt.com"><em><br>
        jcw@copper-mt.com</em></a></td>
        <td>John led the establishment of Copper Mountain Financial Group,
        Inc. as an independent company in the summer of 1995.
        Prior to his involvement with Copper Mountain, he was a
        part owner, board member and on the management team for
        The Crabbe Huson Group, where he oversaw activities of
        its Pacific Northwest Trust Co. In forming Copper Mountain, John
        has positioned the company to provide local, integrated financial management services
        to retirement plans and high net worth individuals in the
        Northwest and Rocky Mountain States. John earned his MBA
        degree in Finance from the University of Chicago and his
        BA from the University of Southern California. He began
        his career as a securities attorney with a Portland-based
        legal firm. He is active in his community, serving on the
        Boards of Emanuel Hospital, Catlin Gabel School, and the
        Portland Youth Philharmonic.</td>
        <td><a href="mailto:jcm@copper-mt.com"></a>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em>Richard (Rick) J. Meigs, Chief Operating Officer<br>
        <br>
        E-mail address: </em><a href="mailto:rjm@copper-mt.com"><em><br>
        rjm@copper-mt.com</em></a></td>
        <td>Rick joined The Crabbe Huson Group in the spring of
        1988 to manage Pacific Northwest Trust Company activities.
        In the summer of 1995, he joined John Wheeler in creating Copper Mountain
        as an independent company offering services to retirement plans
        and high net worth individuals. Prior to his association with
        Copper Mountain, Rick held numerous key management positions
        at First Interstate Bank, including manager of the bank's $10
        billion Master Trustee and Custodial Group. Rick is a
        native of Oregon and a graduate of the School for Bank Administration
        at the University of Wisconsin specializing in Trust and Financial Services.
        He currently serves on the Oregon Bankers Association's legislative committee and
        is active in Church and non-profit organizations.</td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em>Sandra C. Mico, Director of Marketing<br>
        <br>
        E-mail address:</em><a href="mailto:scm@copper-mt.com"><em><br>
        scm@copper-mt.com</em></a></td>
        <td>Sandy joined Copper Mountain to oversee sales and
        marketing activities in April, 1995. Prior to this, she
        served as Senior Vice President and Northwest Regional Sales Manager
        for First Interstate Bank's Trust Group. Sandy started
        her financial career at Wells Fargo Bank in the Personal Asset Management group
        in 1971, returning to Oregon in 1981 when she joined First Interstate Bank.
        She is a graduate of Oregon State University and the
        Pacific Coast Banking School. Sandy is active in<b> </b>the Bank Marketing Association and
        on the Board of Directors for the March of Dimes.</td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em>Paul Douthit, Chief Financial
        Officer<br>
        <br>
        E-mail address:</em><a href="mailto:spd@copper-mt.com"><em><br>
        spd@copper-mt.com</em></a></td>
        <td>A graduate of the University of Southern California, Paul
        is a CPA with broad experience in the financial services
        and investment industries. Prior to joining Copper Mountain, Paul
        was with the Washington Department of Labor and Industries
        as Chief Financial Officer for the Workers Compensation
        Fund. His financial career also includes eight years in
        the private sector and almost ten years with Coopers
        &amp; Lybrand as audit manager. <font size="3">Paul is a
        member of the AICPA and the Oregon Society of CPAs.</font></td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
</table>

