content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>Copper Mountain WealthTrack</title>
</head>

<body background="images/watchart.gif">

<h2 align="center"><a href="index.html"><img
src="images/cmlogot.gif" alt="Copper Mountain Financial Group"
border="0" width="652" height="74"></a></h2>

<p><br>
</p>

<h3>WealthTrack, the best packaged 401(k) product available!</h3>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<blockquote>
    <h3>&quot;Unless they become significantly more frugal, many
    members of the Baby Boom generation will be forced to accept
    dramatically lower standards of living during retirement, or
    else forego retirement altogether. </h3>
    <p>&quot;In the worst case scenarios, Baby Boomers are saving
    less than one-tenth of what is required to avoid a
    potentially precipitous decline in their standard of living
    after retirement. </p>
    <p>&quot;Realistic assumptions about the fiscal outlook for
    the twenty-first century imply the savings crisis is far
    worse than previously imagined.&quot;*</p>
</blockquote>

<h6>*Source: &quot;The Merrill Lynch Baby Boom Retirement
Index&quot; prepared by: Dr. B. Douglas Bernheim, Stanford
University July, 1994.</h6>

<hr>

<p><b><i>WHETHER YOU HAVE</i></b> a retirement plan or not,
chances are you've given some thought lately to the subject of
retirement ... given all the talk, who can avoid it? </p>

<p>We're thinking about it, too. And we're doing something about
it. </p>

<p>Too many of today's retirement plans simply don't meet the
needs of business owners and their employees. Investment choices
are limited or perform poorly. Service is often spotty.
Information is hard to come by. Regulations are confusing and
constantly proliferating. </p>

<p>With obstacles like these, it's no wonder employees aren't
saving more. </p>

<p align="center">And that's where our real concern comes in.
None of us is getting younger. And in matters of investment... </p>

<h3 align="center">...time is of the essence.</h3>

<p>Creating a retirement nest egg takes time. And time is rapidly
running out for a significant portion of our population. For all
these reasons we've designed WealthTrack to precisely address the
shortfalls of so many retirement plans in place today. </p>

<hr>

<p align="center"><b>INVESTMENTS THAT PERFORM</b> </p>

<hr>

<p>Face it. With a BEWILDERING number of investment options in
the marketplace today, employers and participants are paralyzed
by too many choices. We've made it elegantly simple. WealthTrack
offers two smart and simple choices: </p>

<ul>
    <li>You can choose from among the top retirement plan money
        managers in the nation, carefully screened and monitored
        by WealthTrack's senior investment professionals. </li>
</ul>

<p><b>OR</b> </p>

<ul>
    <li>You can select from a list of no-load mutual funds
        defined by Morningstar as the nation's most consistent
        top long-term performers. </li>
</ul>

<p>We reduced a staggering array of choices to those few money
managers who are among the best on the planet. We work with you
to tailor the mix of funds to fit your plan's specific investment
objectives. </p>

<hr>

<p align="center"><b>EMPLOYEE EDUCATION AND GUIDANCE</b> </p>

<hr>

<p>We get the employee's attention by introducing them to
financial realism. Our education materials get right to the point
seeking to motivate employees to take personal responsibility for
their financial futures--NOW. </p>

<p>We begin our education process with pre-enrollment materials
that include work sheets to help employees determine how much
money they'll need to retire. We build on this information in our
employee enrollment meetings conducted by our marketing
representatives in your work place. </p>

<p>And our quarterly newsletters reinforce three main messages:
it takes TIME, MONEY, and MANAGED RISK to achieve retirement goals. </p>

<p>We know that employees are more likely to maximize their
retirement investments if they are kept well informed about their
accounts. That's why we've designed our quarterly participant
statement to summarize investment activity and the performance of
each investment choice. </p>

<p>We also offer a 24-hour voice response system that will
provide full on demand account information to your employees. </p>

<hr>

<p align="center"><b>OPERATIONAL SIMPLICITY AND EFFICIENCY</b> </p>

<hr>

<p>We know it's not easy to move a retirement plan. But
WealthTrack makes it both economically worthwhile and easy. Our
extensive use of technology markedly reduces administrative time.
And because it's available to your third-party record keeper, it
can reduce their bills to you as well. </p>

<p>You and all plan participants have 24 hour-a-day electronic
access to updated data on every plan account and all plan assets.
Quarterly, simple-to-read, statements for, participants break out
all participant investments by fund and also show a current asset
allocation profile of their entire retirement account. </p>

<p>WealthTrack's proprietary payroll deduction software automates
the tracking of all employee contributions and investment
elections, a huge reduction in labor for your office. And to
bring WealthTrack to your firm, we field a dedicated and able
team of administrative, operational and marketing staff to work
with your people to make the transfer as flawless as possible. </p>

<hr>

<p align="center"><b>REGULATORY COMPLIANCE</b> </p>

<hr>

<p>Where there are pension plans, there are details--and usually
lots of them. We handle them with ease. Be they custody,
administrative or trustee services, you get the support and
results you expect from a top line firm. </p>

<p>Through TrustMark, we give your third-party administrator easy
access to the information needed to complete all regulatory tests
and reports. And we've seen to it that our educational programs
and investment choices meet 404(c) requirements. </p>

<p>We deliver these services with a strong knowledge of your
legal and fiduciary responsibilities so you can be assured your
pension plan is in compliance with current and evolving
government standards. </p>

<hr>

<p align="center"><b>AFFORDABILITY</b> </p>

<hr>

<p>The WealthTrack program is affordably priced in accord with
the size of your plan. All WealthTrack clients receive our
comprehensive package of services including: </p>

<ul>
    <li>Plan Management &amp; Consultation Services. </li>
    <li>Investment Management Services. </li>
    <li>Employee Education &amp; Communications Programs. </li>
    <li>Daily Account Valuation Services. </li>
    <li>Custody &amp; Trustee Services. </li>
</ul>

<p>Everything you and your plan need in one experienced team,
supported by the best technology in the business and focused
aggressively on ensuring that your employees get the support they
need to prepare financially for a successful retirement. </p>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

