<h3>COPPER MOUNTAIN FINANCIAL GROUP <br>
ADDS NORTHWEST MARKETING PROFESSIONAL</h3>

<p>August 28, 1996-- (Portland, OR) -- Copper Mountain Financial
Group, Inc. announced today the addition of Daniel Clark to its
Seattle office as marketing professional. </p>

<p>Clark joins Copper Mountain from CIGNA, where he was a vice
president with their Retirement and Investment Services Division.
Prior to CIGNA, his investment career included positions at
Howard Johnson &amp; Company and six years as a Financial Consultant
and Retirement Plan Specialist with Merrill Lynch. He holds both
an M.A. and B.A. from Washington University in St. Louis and The University
of Washington respectively. Clark will handle marketing and
client services for the Northwest region. </p>

<p>Copper Mountain Financial Group is a wealth building
investment services company based in Portland, Oregon. Originally
founded in 1981 as part of The Crabbe Huson Group, Copper
Mountain became an independent firm in 1995 offering investment advisory
and financial services for corporate pension plans and
individuals. With additional offices in Bend and Eugene, Oregon,
as well as Seattle and Yakima, Washington, Copper Mountain
employs more than 70 people and oversees over $4 billion in
assets. </p>

