<h3>COPPER MOUNTAIN FINANCIAL GROUP ADDS <br>
TRUSTMARK PROFESSIONAL</h3>

<p>September 3, 1996-- (Portland, OR) -- Copper Mountain
Financial Group, Inc. announced today the addition of Barbara
Fuentes to its Portland office. Fuentes joined the firm as
Assistant Manager - WealthTrack, Copper Mountain's 401k
retirement product. </p>

<p>Fuentes joins Copper Mountain from SPS Consulting, a division
of Union Bank of California. Her expertise is in plan
administration and consulting for plan conversions on the
TrustMark daily system. TrustMark is the preeminent share-based
participant accounting system for daily retirement plan
recordkeeping. </p>

<p>Copper Mountain Financial Group is a wealth building
investment services company based in Portland, Oregon. Originally
founded in 1981 as part of The Crabbe Huson Group, Copper
Mountain became an independent firm in 1995 offering investment
advisory and financial services for corporate pension plans and
individuals. With additional offices in Bend and Eugene, Oregon,
as well as Seattle and Yakima, Washington, Copper Mountain
employs more than 70 people and oversees over $4 billion in
assets. </p>

