<h3>PORTLAND COMPANY UNVEILS INTERNET MUTUAL FUND INFO
CLEARINGHOUSE</h3>

<p>September 13, 1996-- (Portland, OR) -- Web savvy investors
hungry for quick information on the vast universe of mutual funds
available today can now simply make a quick stop at the Copper
Mountain Financial Group's new mutual fund link
(www.copper-mt.com). </p>

<p>The link is one of many new additions to the Portland-based
investment company's Internet Web site designed to give their
clients and other curious investors quicker, easier access to
fund performance figures and background information. </p>

<p>&quot;There are more than 6,000 mutual funds available
today,&quot; says Copper Mountain Chief Operating Officer Rick
Meigs. &quot;Things are happening so quickly in the mutual fund
arena that most people have a hard time keeping up with all
that's available. This new link gives our clients and anyone else
who is curious a new tool to help them stay on top of their
investment opportunities.&quot; </p>

<p>In addition to the mutual fund link, Copper Mountain has added
Net Asset Value ~NAV) performance figures on its commingled
pooled funds, which are updated daily, as well as quarterly
performance figures for all of their mutual fund offerings. </p>

<p>Copper Mountain Financial Group is a wealth building
investment services company based in Portland, Oregon. Originally
founded in 1981 as part of The Crabbe Huson Group, Copper
Mountain became an independent firm in 1995 offering investment
advisory and financial services for corporate pension plans and
individuals. With additional offices in Bend and Eugene, Oregon
as well as Seattle and Yakima, Washington, Copper Mountain
employs more than 70 people and oversees more than $4 billion in
assets. </p>

