<h3>FINANCIAL TRADE GROUP HONORS TWO COPPER MOUNTAIN FINANCIAL<br>
GROUP EXECUTIVES</h3>

<p>September 13, 1996-- (Portland, OR) Sallie Olson and Tim West,
of Portland's Copper Mountain Financial Group were both honored recently
by the American Bankers Association (ABA) and one of its
affiliates for completion of continuing education courses. </p>

<p>Olson and West were awarded the Employee Benefit Certified
Trust Professional (EBCTP) designation from the Institute of
Certified Bankers, a non-profit organization sponsored by the
ABA. Additionally, Olson, last week, received her diploma for
completing the ABA's National Employee Benefit Trust School. </p>

<p>The EBCTP designation is awarded to individuals who
demonstrate excellence in the field of employee benefits trust.
To qualify for certification, individuals must achieve specific
levels of experience and knowledge in the employee benefits trust
profession, and sign an ethics statement. </p>

<p>Copper Mountain Financial Group is a wealth building
investment services company based in Portland, Oregon. Originally
founded in 1981 as part of The Crabbe Huson Group, Copper
Mountain became an independent firm in 1995 offering investment
advisory and financial services for corporate pension plans and
individuals. With additional offices in Bend and Eugene, Oregon
as well as Seattle and Yakima, Washington, Copper Mountain
employs more than 70 people and oversees more than $4 billion in
assets. </p>

