<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Cohen, Klingenstein &amp; Marks</h2>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>The principals of Cohen, Klingenstein &amp; Marks
        worked together for many years before founding the firm
        in 1981, George Cohen and Richard Marks met at M.I.T. in
        1961 and later worked together on a number of analytical
        projects using their quantitative skills. <p>Initially,
        Cohen, Klingenstein &amp; Marks developed and marketed
        comprehensive investment management software for money
        managers and consulted on a broad range of projects
        including international asset allocation, options
        valuation, oil price analysis, multi-currency accounting
        and performance measurement. In 1987, the firm began
        managing money which is now its sole business. </p>
        <p>Cohen, Klingenstein &amp; Marks is a
        large-capitalization, growth stock manager with a
        disciplined three-step investment approach. First, a
        top-down economic view is developed, defining the
        character of the portfolio. Second, proprietary
        quantitative screens are run to produce candidates for
        inclusion in the portfolio. Third, traditional
        fundamental analysis is applied to that short list to
        determine the selected stock holdings. </p>
        <p>Cohen, Klingenstein &amp; Marks believes that the next
        couple of decades will favor growth stock investing. Some
        factors leading to that conclusion are the maturing of
        the baby boomers, a group which will be forced to save
        more for their retirement needs; the end of the Cold War,
        which will favorably redirect resources; the opening of
        new financial markets globally; and the acceleration of
        technological and other productivity advances. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Large Cap Growth </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$350 million </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Vehicles:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Equity Commingled Pooled Fund </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Year Founded:</strong></em></td>
        <td>1981 </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Staff:</strong></em></td>
        <td>A total of 5 including 3 investment professionals, 2
        administrative. </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Office:</strong></em></td>
