<h2>Equinox Capital Management</h2>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Formed in 1989, Equinox Capital Management is an
        independent investment advisor providing equity portfolio
        management to tax-exempt and other large clients.
        Equinox's investment team has worked together over a
        number of years and has maintained a consistent
        investment philosophy throughout. <p>The Equinox
        philosophy is to provide consistent returns that exceed
        both the S&amp;P 500 and other value managers over the
        longer term. This is accomplished with a conservative
        approach that limits downside volatility yet perform's
        well during times that its style is in favor. This is
        accomplished by identifying and investing in inexpensive
        companies with low risk but solid longer term potential. </p>
        <p>Equinox places, high emphasis on the sell discipline
        as a key component to its strategy. Securities are
        selected from a total universe of 1,000 companies which
        are initially screened via a proprietary quantitative
        model and ranked according to several criteria. The top
        20% of these companies represents the &quot;buy
        list&quot; of potential companies, which are then
        subjected to rigorous fundamental research to determine
        potential earnings growth. </p>
        <p>Portfolios are diversified broadly among 15 industry
        sectors and contain approximately 60 securities. Risk controls
        are extensive and involve an emphasis on financially
        strong, inexpensive companies while stressing diversification,
        in-depth fundamental knowledge of portfolio holdings, and
        a unique approach to selling companies that reach full
        valuation. Equinox has a thorough, focused process. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Large Cap Value </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$4.7 Billion </td>
