<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Global Asset Management, Inc.</h2>

<p><a href="http://www.usinfo.gam.com">Link to the GAM WWW site.</a> </p>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Global Asset Management, Inc. is an international
        equity and bond investment firm. Since its founding in
        1983, it has provided money management and investment
        opportunities for investors worldwide who seek long-term capital
        appreciation. <p>The investment approach of Global Asset
        Management focuses on investing at least 65% of its
        portfolio in equity securities in a minimum of three
        foreign countries, excluding the United States. These
        investments are diversified among countries to reduce the
        effect of downturns in any single country or company. It
        may invest a substantial portion of assets in debt
        securities, but no more than 5% of these debt securities
        will be rated below investment grade. </p>
        <p>Using a top-down, macro economic approach this fund
        manager identifies value in markets, sectors and stocks. By
        first developing a broad analysis of various countries
        and their interest rates and growth, industry sectors are then
        selected that are projected to benefit from economic
        trends. This provides the framework in which to identify specific
        stocks for the portfolio. Stock positions are generally
        held for nine months to two years. </p>
        <p>The diversification that this Fund provides by
        investing in foreign markets offers excellent
        opportunities for growth. Global investing may improve a
        portfolio's return without increasing the risk by gaining
        exposure to markets with higher returns, while reducing
        the effects of any single country's market downturn. </p>
        <p>The Fund managers concentrate on managing assets and
        are strategically located in nine locations worldwide, allowing
        them to conduct ongoing on-site company evaluations. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Top-down, Global Value </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$8.9 Billion </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Vehicles:</strong></em></td>
        <td>International Commingled Pooled Fund </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Year Founded:</strong></em></td>
        <td>1983 </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Staff:</strong></em></td>
        <td>A total of 389 including 36 investment professionals
        and portfolio managers located worldwide. </td>
    </tr>
