<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Kopp Investment Advisors</h2>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Based in Minneapolis, Kopp Investment Advisors is an
        independent money management firm. Utilizing two key operating
        philosophies, Kopp believes it is possible to achieve
        superior results by investing in assets in domestically
        based emerging company growth stocks. These growth stocks
        are defined as having small to medium market
        capitalization and significant potential for accelerated
        earnings growth. Kopp methodically adheres to the basics
        of sound money management - investing in companies, not
        in the stock market - to guide them through their
        five-step analysis and selection process. <p>By employing
        a bottom up quantitative approach, Kopp reviews over 120
        companies that are undervalued in their current business,
        industry sector or historical standards. The fundamental
        analysis for each company selection includes: earnings
        growth, price/earnings ratio, price/sales ratio, and
        R&amp;D spending. Ultimately, the portfolio will consist
        of approximately 30 - 40 stocks. An investment associated
        with this style of management results in stock selections
        that may trade more infrequently because of their smaller
        market capitalization and may therefore have more limited
        public float. Therefore, such an investment may incur
        greater volatility and stock illiquidity than the market
        as a whole. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Emerging Growth </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$2.5 billion </td>
    </tr>
