<head>
<title>Copper Mountain Financial Group - Morley Capital</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">

<p align="center"><a href="index.html"><img src="images/cmlogot.gif" border="0" width="652" height="74"></a> </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Morley Capital Management, Inc.</h2>

<p><a href="http://www.morley.com">Link to the Morley Capital Management
WWW site.</a> </p>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Since 1982, Morley Capital Management has pioneered
        the use of managed stable asset portfolios, developing
        the first stable value pooled fund approved by the U.S.
        Comptroller of the Currency. The principal objectives of
        this stable value management style are to provide
        participants with predictable income, capital
        preservation, and low risk to market price volatility.
        Morley achieves these objectives by investing in
        fixed-term investment or insurance contracts issued by
        life insurance companies, banks and other financial
        institutions, and in cash and cash equivalents. <p>To
        achieve stability of asset values, Morley has negotiated
        agreements with all issuers to its commingled funds which
        permit participant transfers or withdrawals to be taken
        at contract value, with no penalties or market-value adjustments.
        Thus, a participant's interest in the find will normally
        be carried at contract value plus accrued interest. </p>
        <p>In addition to reviewing all investment decisions made
        by the institutions to ensure the integrity of the
        investments, Morley utilizes rigorous research, credit
        analysis and diversification programs to minimize and
        spread risk. If rated, investments or issuers must have a
        rating of &quot;A&quot; or better by Moody's, Standard
        &amp; Poor's, or Duff &amp; Phelps at the time of
        purchase. The current average credit quality 6f Morley's
        commingled funds is AA+. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Stable Value Investments </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$7.0 billion </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Vehicles:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Commingled Pooled Fund </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Year Founded:</strong></em></td>
        <td>1982 </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Staff:</strong></em></td>
        <td>46 </td>
    </tr>
