<title>Copper Mountain Financial Group - Pacific Investment Management Company</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">

<p align="center"><a href="index.html"><img
src="images/cmlogot.gif" border="0" width="652" height="74"></a> </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Pacific Investment Management Company</h2>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Pacific Investment Management Company (PIMCO) is a
        leading institutional fixed income money manager. Established
        in 1971 as a subsidiary of Pacific Mutual, PIMCO offers
        investment management of employee benefit plans,
        endowments and foundations. <p>PIMCO's investment
        philosophy relies on following a portfolio strategy that
        is driven by longer-term sector trends and by avoiding
        extreme swings in maturity/duration of the portfolio. The
        Total Return Fund is an intermediate maturity bond
        portfolio with the objective of maximizing total return
        and minimizing volatility. The Fund has an average
        duration ranging between three and six years and is
        actively managed to seek returns exceeding the bond
        market as a whole. Investments are made in fixed income
        securities and can include obligations of the U.S.
        Government, corporate debt securities, mortgage and other
        asset-backed securities, and money market instruments. </p>
        <p>PIMCO's consistent results stem from their investment
        philosophy and process. With a portfolio consisting of a mixture
        of long and short bonds, and bond quality ranging from A
        to Aa, the performance returns are more steady and the
        volatility factor is greatly reduced.</p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Active Decision Making with long-term Focus </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$68.5 billion </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Vehicles:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Fixed Income Commingled Pooled Funds </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Year Founded:</strong></em></td>
        <td>1971 </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Staff:</strong></em></td>
        <td>259: Investment Professionals: 18; Administrative:
        30; Support: 211. </td>
