<h2>The Crabbe Huson Group, Inc.</h2>

<p><a href="http://www.contrarian.com">Link to the Crabbe Huson
WWW site.</a> </p>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Crabbe Huson is a value-oriented, disciplined
        contrarian money manager. Since their founding in 1980,
        they have consistently followed this highly successful
        investment style. Contrarian investing can be described
        as looking for the most attractive investment
        opportunities in quality companies that have temporarily
        fallen out of favor with the general market. So while
        most money managers view an asset that is rising in price
        as being attractive, Crabbe Huson looks for the asset
        that is declining in price as a potentially attractive
        buying opportunity. <p>Crabbe Huson's experienced
        investment team attentively watches for such
        opportunities. Their objective is to buy securities just
        before they hit their lows and then ride them back up to
        predetermined sell points. This philosophy is applied
        successfully to both large and small-cap equities. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Contrarian </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$4.1 Billion </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Vehicles:</strong></em></td>
