<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Wanger Asset Management. L.P.</h2>

<p><img src="images/pookline.gif" width="722" height="13"> </p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Philosophy:</strong></em></td>
        <td>The Acorn International Fund, founded in 1992 and
        managed by Wanger Asset Management, L.P., is located in Chicago,
        Illinois. This fund seeks long-term capital growth
        through investments in small to medium-sized international companies. <p>The
        managers of this international fund invest at least 75%
        of assets in foreign securities but may invest in corporate
        or government obligations or hold cash or cash
        equivalents. Selected investments are chosen based on
        superior growth potential, financial strength and
        stability, strong management and fundamental value. </p>
        <p>Using a top down approach, the fund looks for
        companies that will benefit from favorable long-term
        social, economic or political trends. The foreign
        securities may be traded in either mature or emerging
        markets and are held for a longer time horizon, at least
        3 to 5 years, to maximize return potential. The portfolio
        is well diversified in a minimum of three countries and
        no one country takes up more than 11% of the investments. </p>
        <p>The diversification that this Fund provides by
        investing in foreign markets offers excellent
        opportunities for growth. Global investing may improve a
        portfolio's return without increasing the risk by gaining
        exposure to markets with higher returns, while reducing
        the effects of any single country's market downturn. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Style:</strong></em></td>
        <td>Top-down, International Capital Growth </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Assets Under Management:</strong></em></td>
        <td>$1.4 Billion </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><em><strong>Investment Vehicles:</strong></em></td>
