<font size=2><img src="21_m.gif" align=left border=1 hspace=6 width=360 height=443>
Johnathan Thornton captured some of the most compelling images of the War by traveling with combat units. His images earned Thornton a Pulitzer Prize nomination, but he was wounded several times and once given no hope for survival. Thornton's photographs document the battles of the Posavina Corridor in northern Bosnia where Serbs pushing toward Sarajevo, engaged in brutal fighting.</p>

