<font face="arial, helvetica" color="00BB65" size=5><b>
if youve come this far,<br>youve got the fetish, dude</b><br><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#B3B8A5" size=2><b>
so what is an underwear fetish? is it a bad thing? 
<br><br>
a fetish is defined by psychologists as a form of sexual deviance involving erotic attachment to an inanimate object. in anthropology, a fetish is a magic charm packed with spiritual powers and used in tribal cultures as well as so-called civilized societies. sigmund freud wrote about the fetish in which the savage sees the embodiment of his god. well said, ziggy. 
<br><br>
the phenomenon occurs almost exclusively among men, and the most common fetishes are articles of clothing  most often shoes and underwear.
<br><br>
david sebringsil, at his web site <a href="http://members.aol.com/sebringsil/sex.htm">understanding male sexuality</a>, writes . . .<br><br>
<blockquote>
those with underwear fetishes appear to be about equally divided between those who have a preference for briefs, bikinis and thongs, and those who have a preference for boxer shorts. the group interested in boxer style shorts seem disinterested in other underwear styles, and vice versa. 
<br><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#00BB65" size=4><b>straight, gay or what?</b><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#B3B8A5" size=2><b>
based on internet sites and newsgroup activity, it may appear that underwear fetishes are largely a gay activity, but straights engage in these activities as well. i have visited with very happily married men whose wives not only know about the underwear fetish, but help their husbands pick out underwear that is particularly arousing to them  the underwear is simply part of the overall sexual chemistry between man and wife. 
<br><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#00BB65" size=4><b>trading briefs</b><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#B3B8A5" size=2><b>
one unique activity engaged in my many men with underwear fetishes is underwear trading. this activity appears to take on a particular importance in gay society. the newsgroups are filled with requests by gay men to trade underwear, jock-straps or other similar garments. though there may be straight men who also engage in this activity, i have yet to hear from one. 
<br><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#00BB65" size=4><b>collecting underwear</b><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#B3B8A5" size=2><b>
among underwear traders are specialists. some prefer trading underwear or jockstraps that are new and still in the original packaging, much as someone might collect coins or model trains. they may catalog their collection in detail for other participants to read.  other men, gays primarily, are interested in trading underwear, jockstraps or swimwear that are used. a number of men have admitted to stealing (they call it liberating) these kinds of items from laundry rooms or lockerrooms when they are left unattended. 
<br><br>
</blockquote>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#00BB65" size=4><b>doing the underwear dance</b><br>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#B3B8A5" size=2><b>
many gay bars have underwear nights in which men dress only in underwear  its the lockerroom gag all over again, but with cool music and a club full of men who share a specific preference.
<br><br>
but whos got time to be judgemental? the underwear fetish is one of those few erotic experiences that all men, straight or gay, share. if youre one, enjoy it. its part of what makes you an individual. and theres lots of other guys out there whove got it too, and dig it  big time.
</td></table>

