<FONT face="arial, helvetica" SIZE=2><b>
<img src="tarzan.jpg" width=120 height=149
align=left vspace=3 border=0 hspace=5 alt=""><p>
from fig leaves to spandex, man has been engaged in a coverup ever since adam. styles have changed, but the concept remains the same, whether a codpiece, posing strap, thong, jock or briefs. 
<p>
it began with the loincloth which gave us endless men-in-their-underwear movies  from tarzan to rapa nui. <a href="jungleboy.html">
<img src="jungleboy_sm.jpg" width=115 height=165
align=right vspace=3 border=0 hspace=0 alt=""></a>the loincloth morphed into a skirt in ancient egypt and the western pacific. but out in indonesia, indigenous dudes still tie on a gourd. the bigger the better. 
