<TD valign=top align=left><font face="arial, helvetica" size=2 color="#B860B7"><b>
<img src="belle_m.gif" width=54 height=32 align=left vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0>ichael labelle has been moving around a lot. los angeles, las vegas, and now back to his native qubec  in laval, in the laurentian mountain countryside near montreal. the men drawn by michael labelle have been moving around, too. into orbit, across the bay on battle manoeuvers, and out buying underwear at jockworld, a store that represents a total breakthrough in retailing, to say the least.
<br><br>
fans of michael labelle will understand. for five years, labelle has been creating hot cowboys, athletes, muscle-mad robots, construction dudes and more under his belle iconix studio banner. now, he turns them loose in a world of their own in his most recent work, a 44-page comic labelle calls <u>utopolis,</u> <font color="#B860B7">his first work in linear storytelling. 
<br><br>
<font color="#D07831">
<img src="belle_f.gif" width=21 height=43 align=left vspace=0 hspace=2 border=0>or comix fans, putting the labelle men into stories, and hearing them speak  well its the biggest thing since garbo talked. in episode one, you approach <u>utopolis</u> from low orbit where a lone, buzzcut, jockstrapped astronaut is teleconferencing with an buddy on the planet below. 
<br><br>
i'm ready for bedtime stories, says the stud, whats going on down there where everything always is what is appears to be? hold your orbit, space brother, replies his pal, as he uploads an adventure feed from the surface.
<br><br>
a panorama of life on <u>utopolis</u> begins to unfold. a young married couple at the artificial insemination clinic of dr. rock t. launcher. a trip to an underwear store with some hard-to-fit big boyz. a military conflict resolved with sheer musclepower. even the commercials on <u>utopolis</u> are cool. 
<br><br>

hey duncan, an off-camera announcer calls to a star quarterback getting his tit stroked by a big-boobed babe sitting on the jocks prize car, you just won the chicks and vette contest. what are you going to do next? take my buddy for a spin, replies duncan. ah, <u>utopolis.</u> beam me up, duncan. 
<br><br>
<font color="#52AFB7">
<img src="belle_l.gif" width=17 height=43 align=left vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0>abelle is currently developing a sequel that includes the backstory of utopolis while studying 3d animation at icari, in old montreal, where the software program softimage was created.
<br><br>
i've always been an artist, i knew that from day one, says labelle in accent qubec. i studied architecture at the university of montreal, then moved into fine art and graphic art at concordia university in montreal. 
<br><br>
labelle spent several years studying body culture in los angeles while painting those billboard-size blow-ups of album covers seen plastered all over tower records. but it was l.a.s traffic patterns that labelle was studing in detail.
<br><br>
my first art was an obsession with freeways and urban design which i saw as a puzzle. that's what brought me to l.a., it was the first city in our time to be built specifically to accomodate traffic grids.</td>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=449 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=15>
<TD width=324 valign=bottom align=right>
<img src="belle_sub1.gif" width=324 height=19 align=bottom vspace=0 hspace=0 border=0><p>
<font face="arial, helvetica" color="#4DD037" size=2><b>
when i began realizing that i was attracted to men for their power and masculinity, i started sketching men, but was shy about it. it took many years before i began showing my work to anyone. today i'm trying to polish the work, make the guys sexier, more enviable, more powerful  all of it with a lot of humor.<p>
<font color="#C3AD7B">there is social comment here: politics, commercialism, sports and more. i have an opinion about a lot of things, and im putting it all into a synthetic world in a bottle, the more transparent the better.<br>
<a href="belle5.html"><img src="belle5_sm.jpg" width=115 height=157
align=bottom vspace=6 hspace=0 border=0></a><a href="belle6.html"><img src="belle6_sm.jpg" width=209 height=157
align=bottom vspace=6 hspace=0 border=0></a><br><font color="#4DD037">the next revolution is going to be sexual because it's the only thing that remains repressed in us. whatever we're trying to achieve will reveal itself in a world where sex is not as it is today  an object of control, dominance, morality or punishment. once it's all out, allowed to be free of labels, then we can move on.<br>
<font color="#C3AD7B">michael labelle</td>

<TD WIDTH=125 valign=top align=left>
